review_text: Salah satu tempat wisata ataupun kuliner di Semarang. Jalan kesini cukup membuat deg an yaa karena tanjakannya sangat tajam dan jalannya cukup sempit, tapi gak bakal menyesal kalau udh sampai ditempatnya. Tempatnyaa adem dan pemandangannya cakep. Disini juga menyediakan berbagai macam makanan dan minuman, tidak hanya itu saja tapi juga terdapat wifi serta colokan listrik untuk ngecas. Teradapat ruangan indoor dan outdoor. Toiletnya jugaa bersih. Pelayanannya ramah. Setelah pesan menu harus langsung bayar ditempat. Tempatnya luas jadi gak bakal kehabisan tempat kecuali datang pas weekend pasti ramai banget. Tempat parkirnya jugaa ada dibawah dan diatas. Kalau kesini wajib mesen singkong gorengnya, karena lembut bgt. Minum apa aja disini enak apalagi pesan yang panas, jadi pas sama suasananya. Harga cukup mahal tapi okelah dengan pemandagan dan rasanya. Wajib kesini kalau lagi main ke daerah semarang.
review_translated_text: One of the tourist and culinary attractions in Semarang. The road here is quite nerve-wracking because the incline is very sharp and the road is quite narrow, but you wont regret it once you get there. The place is cool and the view is beautiful. It also provides various kinds of food and drinks, not only that, but there is also wifi and electric sockets for charging. There are indoor and outdoor rooms. The toilet is also clean. The service is friendly. After ordering the menu you have to pay immediately on the spot. The place is spacious so you wont run out of space unless you come on the weekend and it will be very busy. There are also parking spaces below and above. If you come here, you must order the fried cassava, because its really soft. Anything you drink here is delicious, especially if you order something hot, so it fits the atmosphere. The price is quite expensive but okay with the view and taste. You must come here if you are playing in the Semarang area.

review_text: The atmosphere is definitely cool, instagrammable, the view is the best, the service is friendly, the food waiting list is still reasonable because its always busy, the food is all delicious, Ive been back here, I dont know how many times, definitely many times because its worth it, because its sitting down Outdoors, I always want to charge my cellphone/something else can be near the cashier, I dont know if its possible indoors

review_text: rute jalan kesini lumayan menantang sih   kalo kesininya bawa motor, keadaan mesin harus oke, bensin harus full, yg motornya matic harus persiapan bawa air buat siram mtr bagian depan (rem). hati2 kalo bawa motor karna jalanannya ga semulus di jalan raya   tp kalo udah sampe sini jadi terbayarkan sama view untuk harga makanan ya menurutku yg kaum mendang mending ini emang cukup mahal. kesini juga harus persiapan uang juga ya ges yaa pas aku sama temen2 kesini sih langsung hujan (apes)   yg ga kuat dingin aku saranin pake jaket aga tebel ya tempat berkunjung buat keluarga seru, tp aku saranin pake mobil ya jgn truk to pondok kopi : kalo boleh saran, jual menu makanan mie kuah/godog yaa, soalnya tempatnya cocok dingin2 gini makan yg berkuah
review_translated_text: The route here is quite challenging   If you come here by motorbike, the engine must be in good condition, the petrol must be full, those with automatic motorbikes must be prepared to bring water to flush the front mtr (brakes). Be careful if you take a motorbike because the roads are not as smooth as on the main road   but once you get here it will pay off with the view As for the price of food, I think the mendang mending are quite expensive. You also have to prepare money here, bro When I and my friends came here it immediately started raining (unfortunately)   If you cant stand the cold, I suggest you wear a thicker jacket. A fun place to visit for families, but I recommend using a car, not a truck to Pondok Kopi: If I may suggest, sell a menu of noodle soup/godog, because the place is suitable for cold weather like eating soup

review_translated_text: the rooms are okay..the waiters are okay..the food in the restaurant is okay..its a shame..we were very disappointed when our children were so excited to try playing in the swimming pool..as soon as we got closer the officers approached us..it is forbidden to enter the pool if you are wearing a t-shirt. .you have to wear a swimsuit..as a result, the enthusiastic and cheerful children who want to play become sad and disappointed..maybe I understand if that has become the SOP for the swimming pool..but what makes me feel very disappointed..why are other guests allowed to enter? going into the pool wearing a t-shirt...why are my children the only ones prohibited???? I have several photos of visitors wearing t-shirts and its not prohibited at all... actually there are still lots... but its not nice to take photos

review_text: stayed for 3 nights with big family (12 pax adults) great view. there are some outbond activities. swimming pool is being cleaned twice a week & doesnt contain chlorine. good for kids. need some improvements for wheelchair and elderly facilities. 1st night: need improvement in family room (8pax capacity) in term of cleanliness, and shower access. bathroom doors cant be closed. one-way vision glass door was installed backwards! people from outside could see when youre taking shower. the bed was old and not firm. ==== 2nd & 3rd night: we moved to deluxe room for 4 pax. (booked 3 rooms) better facilities, better view, beds were firm and nice. overall, friendly staffs, kid-friendly facilities, but not for elderly as there are many stairs to your room (and cant be accessed ny car) ==== parking area is huge. breakfast wasnt that good, but edible. dont expect minimarket or other restaurants nearby, as this place is located nearby mountain. but there are food menu provided, price is alright.
overall baguss. price tiket masuknya so affordable! view nya cakep + dinginnn

review_text: Penginapan bagi yg pengen healing dan mendekat dengan alam.Suasana khas pegunungan dg pemandangan menarik. Selain itu jadi satu dg wisata outbound dan kolam renang yg airnya alami. Fasilitas kamar sudah baik, paling suka bisa nonton Netflix gratis.Tetapi yg dirasa kurang tidak adanya lemari di kamar, jadi baju-2 terasa berantakan krn tidak ada tempat utk menyimpan Overall rekomended utk liburan bersama keluarga.
review_translated_text: Accommodation for those who want to heal and get close to nature. Typical mountain atmosphere with interesting views. Apart from that, it is one with outbound tourism and a swimming pool with natural water. The room facilities are good, most like being able to watch Netflix for free. But what is lacking is the lack of a wardrobe in the room, so the clothes feel messy because there is no place to store them. Overall recommended for holidays with the family.

review_text: Tepatnya 30apr - 3 mei 2022. Baru kali ini libur lebaran ngabuur ke Jawa Tengah..    Seruu ya.. macet merayap tapi tetap happy. Meninggalkan jejak di setiap rest area     alias pipis. Lebaran memang paling enaak di daerah ya.. Feel-nya beda.. Kali ini inap di Umbul Sidomukti. Jalanan ke pondok penginapannya kudu hati2. Viewnya cakeep (emang suka pegunungan dan udara dingin).. Seperti di puncak bogor.. Malem pertama bisa menikmati kabut (enaaak banget). Malem kedua zeroo kabut tapi tetap adem. Kamar hanya dapet yg standard, No AC. Karena lokasinya di bawah dan depannya bukan view bukit jd di dalem kamar kurang adem ya.. Review kami : - kamar type Standard : toilet agak gelap ya karena lantai nya warna gelap dan bukan keramik kasar. Jadi kesan kusam dan kurang terawat. Kurang adem karena depan kamar tertutup bangunan aula, bukan view bukit. Shower airnya kurang kencang dan tepat di atas kepala jd kurang nyaman mandinya. - Ranjang bisa utk 4 dewasa dan 2 anak kecil. Bisa tambah extra bed 1. Kamarnya luas deh. - Kami ada pesan makanan fish n chip dan es batu 2 gelas dan BAYAR Loh..!!! Yg disajikan adalah fish n chip pakai LALAT goreng dan es batu dengan gelas yg hitam belum dicuci. Dikomplain ke perugas yg mengantar, dijawab dgn santai sambil senyum2  Maaf kak, sy hanya bertugas mengantar saja.. (ada photonya) Wooww.. Luar biasa ya, memangnya matanya buta ya sampai tdk bisa melihat lalat dan endapan hitam di dalam gelas. Kelihatan sekali kesengajaan dari beberapa pelayan..!!! Akhirnya kami minta ganti ulang semua pesanan. Mengecewakan sekali..!!! - Breakfast cukup variatif. Tdk ada kecap asin    Sambal mantap dan cocok di lidah org jakarta. - Masakan di resto kurang ya.. Nilai 0-5, kami kasih nilai 2. - View dan udara segarnya, mantaap.. Malam pertama berkabut dan dingin (khusus kamar standard harus diluar kamar ya..). Jadi menikmati-nya keluar dari kamar dan naik ke teras type kamar deluxe atau family room. - Pelayanannya cukup lah.. Hanya kelihatan kurang dimanaged dg baik. Kelihatan beberapa pekerja pemalas. Semoga pelayanan yg tidak menghargai customer, bisa segera diperbaiki pekerjanya.
review_translated_text: To be precise, 30 April - 3 May 2022. This is the first time Im going to Central Java for the Eid holiday...    Its exciting... traffic jams creeping up but still happy. Leaving traces in every rest area     aka peeing. Eid is indeed the best in the area... The feeling is different... This time staying at Umbul Sidomukti. You have to be careful on the road to the accommodation. The view is beautiful (I really like mountains and cold air).. Like at the top of Bogor.. The first night you can enjoy the fog (its really nice). The second night there was zero fog but still cool. You only get standard rooms, no AC. Because its located at the bottom and in front of it doesnt have a view of the hill, so inside the room its not cool enough... Our review: - Standard type room: the toilet is a bit dark because the floor is dark and not rough ceramic. So it looks dull and poorly maintained. Its not cool because the front of the room is covered by a hall building, not a view of the hill. The shower water is not strong enough and is right above the head so bathing is not comfortable. - Beds can sleep 4 adults and 2 small children. Can add extra bed 1. The room is spacious. - We will order fish n chips and 2 glasses of ice cubes and PAY..!!! What was served was fish n chips using fried LALAT and ice cubes in a black glass that had not been washed. Complained to the officer who was delivering, he answered casually with a smile, Sorry sis, Im only on duty delivering... (theres a photo) Woww... Thats amazing, his eyes are so blind that he cant see the flies and black deposits in the glass. It looks like it was deliberate on the part of some of the waiters..!!! Finally we asked to replace all orders. So disappointing..!!! - Breakfast is quite varied. There is no soy sauce    The chili sauce is delicious and suits the taste buds of Jakartans. - The food in the restaurant is not good... Score 0-5, we give it 2. - The view and fresh air are great... The first night was foggy and cold (especially for standard rooms, you have to go outside...). So enjoy getting out of the room and going up to the terrace of the deluxe room or family room type. - The service is adequate... It just doesnt seem to be managed well. Looks like some of the workers are lazy. Hopefully the service that doesnt respect customers can be immediately corrected by the workers.

review_text: Kesini bulan Januari 2024, pilih room deluxe. Agak sempit tapi oke lah sesuai harga. Jendela kisi-kisi gak bisa ditutup, ngeri kalo binatang masuk aja. Tapi ngerti kok maksudnya buat sirkulasi udara dan pendingin alam keren banget. Tempatnya banyak anak tangga karena memang di lereng gunung. Cafenya tutup sampai maghrib doank, kalo mau ke resto masih naik lagi sekitar 800m. Kolamnya oke punya, viewnya juara sih. Hati-hati licin di ujung yg anak kecil, kurang ada guard. Breakfest oke lah, sesuai harga. Buat yg bawa mobil, pastikan kondisi prima. Karena naiknya tajem banget dan jalan bukan aspal. Stafnya juga ramah, not bad lah.
review_translated_text: Come here in January 2024, choose a deluxe room. A bit narrow but okay according to the price. The grilled windows cant be closed, its scary if animals come in. But understand what it means for air circulation and natural cooling, which is really cool. The place has lots of stairs because it is on a mountain slope. The cafe is closed until sunset, if you want to go to the restaurant its still up another 800m. The pool is okay, the view is great. Be careful its slippery on the tip for small children, theres not enough guard. Breakfest is okay, according to the price. For those bringing a car, make sure it is in prime condition. Because the rise is very sharp and the road is not asphalt. The staff are also friendly, not bad.

review_text: 2x kesini karena diajak teman kantor.. Suasana di tempat ini enak santai dan udara tidak panas.. Hanya saja makanan yang cocok serta enak di lidah saya hanya ikan bakar dan tahu gorengnya saja  (recommended) Ikan gorengnya keasinan gorengnya terlalu kering jadi keras, kangkungnya juga keasinan dan masih keras, tempe gorengnya B aja, gudangannya enak cuma potongan kubis nya gede2 sampe gak selera makan, karena waktu kubisnya disingkirin kurapnya 1 sendok aja habis jadi cuma banyak di potongan kubisnya.. 2x kesini dan ternyata rasanya konsisten.. Pelayanannya tidak semua helpfull ada yg minta cuma kecap aja bilang gak ada, apa restonya bakar ikan gak pake kecap? pelit amat minta kecap gak ada.. tapi begitu minta sama pelayan yg lain diambilkan (jadi klo minta tolong   ditolak minta sama pelayan yang lain) Untuk harga relatif murah tapi mohon kualitas masakannya diperbaiki biar semuanya enak merata..
review_translated_text: Came here twice because my office friend invited me... The atmosphere in this place is nice and relaxing and the air is not hot... Its just that the only foods that are suitable and delicious to my taste buds are grilled fish and fried tofu  (recommended) The fried fish is too salty and fried too dry so its hard, the kale is also salty and still hard, the fried tempe is just B, the warehouse is delicious but the cabbage pieces are big so I dont have an appetite, because when I put the cabbage away I only used up 1 spoonful of ringworm so there was just a lot of it in the cabbage pieces... Been here twice and it turns out the taste is consistent... The service is not all helpful, some people just ask for soy sauce and they say there isnt any, does the restaurant grill fish without using soy sauce? review_text: beranda eatery legend bgt sudah ada sejak dulu. pelayanannya ramah, cepet dan gercep, atmosphere kaya dirumah nenek aja, enak kok lampunya temaram kalo malam. waktu itu ga cukup ramai.. pas puasa kesininya buat menunya emang menurutku cenderung pricey ya.. (di kebumen) tapi porsinya emang banyak banget dan dijamin kenyang. buat rasa emang selera ya.. 1. chicken teriyaki kayanya aku pesen itu enak dan banyak bgt porsinya 2. dimsum kimbabnya juga enak 3. untuk coffee ukuran normal sugar masih kemanisan di aku, mungkin harus less sugar semoga semakin ramai ya dan berkembang terus..   ga kalah recommended kok sama coffeshop yg lain
review_translated_text: The veranda of the legendary eatery has been around for a long time. the service is friendly, fast and fast, the atmosphere is like being at grandmas house, its nice when the lights are dim at night. At that time it wasnt quite busy... I came here when I was fasting In my opinion, I think the menu tends to be pricey... (in Kebumen) but the portions are really big and you are guaranteed to be full. make it taste really good.. 1. The chicken teriyaki I ordered was delicious and the portion was really big 2. The kimbab dimsum is also delicious 3. For normal size coffee, sugar is still too sweet for me, maybe I should use less sugar I hope it gets busier and continues to grow...   Its no less recommended than other coffeeshops

review_text: Tempatnya bagus dan estetik. Makanannya enak, sudah pernah coba beberapa menunya. Cuma sekarang agak panas dalamnya gak kayak dulu.
review_translated_text: The place is nice and aesthetic. The food is delicious, Ive tried several of the menus. Only now its a bit hot inside, not like before.

review_text: ulasan per tanggal 13 April 2024 hari ini beranda bener-bener dalam performanya yang kacau, pesan makanan jam setengah 12, makanan dateng 1-1.5 jam lamanya. super duper lama dari biasanya. alasannya karna tukang masaknya lagi cuman ada 1 orang. mohon maaf nih, kalau memang cuman ada 1 orang, sebaiknya tutup aja dulu, jangan maksa buka, apalagi ini H+3 lebaran, lagi banyak-banyaknya konsumen, akhirnya keteteran kan. tutup aja dulu dan tunggu semua personel tukang masaknya hadir, gitu loh. tapi kayaknya itu cuman alesan pegawainya aja sih, soalnya pasca saya komplain kenapa lama sekali, trus abis itu langsung dateng semua makanannya cepet. sebelumnya saya komplain karena ada konsumen lain yg pesan pasta sudah di-serve duluan padahal dia baru datang, sementara saya yg udah sejam nunggu belum datang-datang pastanya. udah pasti kelupaan sih untuk itu terpaksa saya rating 1 dari 5, karena sudah banyak buang waktu saya dan keluarga
review_translated_text: review as of April 13, 2024 Today the veranda was really in a mess, ordered food at half past 12, the food arrived within 1-1.5 hours. super duper longer than usual. the reason is because there is only 1 cook. Im sorry, if theres only one person there, its best to just close it first, dont force it to open, especially since its H+3 of Eid, and there are so many customers, youll end up running out, right? Just close it first and wait for all the cooking staff to show up, thats it. but it seems like thats just the employees excuse, because after I complained why it was taking so long, then after that all the food came quickly. Previously, I complained because another customer who ordered pasta had been served first even though he had just arrived, while I had been waiting for an hour and the pasta had not yet arrived. Ive definitely forgotten For this reason, I have to give a rating of 1 out of 5, because it has wasted a lot of my and my familys time

review_text: Tempat yang sangat oke untuk mengajak keluarga, pilihan menu beragam, cukup luas dan ada area bermain di belakang (saat saya datanh hari ini ditutup). Sudah beberapa kali ke sini, pelayanan oke dan cukup cepat meskipun ramai. Hari ini kami pesan nasi goreng rawon iga bakar madu, crispy chicken steak, dan gyu don yakiniku, yang paling oke nasi goreng rawon iga bakar madu, sampai kami pesan untuk take-away. Kekurangannya hanya di mushola yang seadanya dan kurang tertata, toilet yang di belakang tidak sebersih toilet di depan, serta lahan parkir mobil yang hanya ada di pinggir jalan, selebihnya oke :)
review_translated_text: A very good place to invite the family, various menu choices, quite spacious and there is a play area at the back (when I came today it was closed). Have been here several times, the service is okay and quite fast even though it is busy. Today we ordered honey grilled rawon ribs fried rice, crispy chicken steak, and gyu don Yakiniku, the best thing was honey grilled rawon ribs fried rice, until we ordered it for take-away. The only drawbacks are that the prayer room is minimal and not well organized, the toilet at the back is not as clean as the toilet at the front, and the car parking area is only on the side of the road, the rest is okay :)

review_text: Jujur,sempat jadi nongki favorit aku tadi,sudah beberapa x ke cafe ini,ok lah tadinya,ada kendala dikit2 di maklumi ya sm kita,tapi...kemarin sore aku datang lagi niatnya ya mau makan dan juga ngobrol dong, tepatnya tgl 7 jam 4.30 aku datang betiga tepatnya,klo biasanya kita bais makan masih betah nongki dan duduk itu wajarlah ya,dan gak di sangka2 ada salah satu pegawai datang bawak sapu dan serokan..dan dengan santainya dia nyapu persis depan meja kita,dan gak ke bagian meja lain,hanya depan meja kita aja, padahal setau aku gak ada sampah,klopun ada bisa lah nunggu smpk konsumen pulang,itu etikanya,karena sebagian orang menganggap nyapu di saat ada tamu,itu sm aja mengusir kuta secara halus,hello tolong dong owner/ admin siapapun lebih di perhatikan lagi kenyamanan pelanggan,mungkin itu yg terakhir kita datang,next kayaknya gak lagi deh
review_translated_text: Honestly, it used to be my favorite nongki, Ive been to this cafe several times, its okay, there were a few problems, thats understandable for us, but... yesterday afternoon I came again with the intention of eating and chatting, to be precise, on the 7th At 4.30, I came three to be precise, usually when we have finished eating, we still feel comfortable hanging out and sitting, thats normal, and I didnt expect one of the employees to come with a broom and a rake... and he casually swept right in front of our table, and didnt go to the other side. another table, just in front of our table, even though as far as I know theres no rubbish, even if there is, you can wait until the customer comes home, thats the etiquette, because some people consider sweeping when there are guests, thats just gently driving away the kuta, hello, please help. owner/admin whoever pays more attention to customer comfort, maybe that was the last one we came to, next time I dont think so

review_text: Oke pertama kang parkir sepertinya tidak ada ya (CMIIW) soalnya waktu dateng dan pulang ga liat parkirannya mayan banyak menampung motor ya, kalo mobil (depan cafenya) agak sempit sih, tapi karena satu komplek dengan spbu masih bisa diakalin sih lokasi dekat alun-alun serta terdapat alfamart dan spbu di sampingnya ketika masuk kita akan menemukan meja berisi menu dan sebuah alat tulis untuk mencatat pesanan baru kemudian ke kasir. Tapi seprtinya bisa juga langsung pesan menu di kasir jika antrian sepi, biar ngga mengganggu antrian better ditulis dulu aja waktu itu pesan Kopi Teman Hati (23K) alias kopi klepon. Baru pertama sih nyoba kopi klepon gitu enak-enak aja hehe. untuk tempatnya tersedia 2 lantai, kalau mau lebih fokus enak lantai 2 sih walau tetep ada suara musik. Stopkontak di lantai 2 kurang menyeluruh menurutku, mungkin bisa tanya pegawai enaknya gimana. kalau lagi sepi sih aman ya wkwk. Terus wifinya menurut saya sedang sih tidak yang wah atau jelek. Toilet dan mushola ada di lantai 2 yah.
review_translated_text: OK, first of all, there doesnt seem to be any parking, right (CMIIW) because when you come and go you cant see it The parking lot can accommodate a lot of motorbikes, but for cars (in front of the cafe) its a bit narrow, but because its in the same complex as a gas station, you can still get around it. The location is near the main square and there is an Alfamart and gas station next to it When we enter we will find a table containing a menu and a stationery to record new orders and then go to the cashier. But it looks like you can also order the menu directly at the cashier if the queue is quiet, so it doesnt disrupt the queue, its better to just write it down first. At that time, I ordered Kopi Teman Hati (23K) aka Klepon coffee. This is the first time Ive tried Klepon coffee, its really delicious, hehe. There are 2 floors available for the place, if you want to focus more, the 2nd floor is nice even though there is still music. In my opinion, the power outlets on the 2nd floor are not comprehensive enough, maybe you can ask the staff how good they are. If its quiet, its safe, okay? Then, in my opinion, the wifi is not good or bad. The toilet and prayer room are on the 2nd floor.

review_text: Nyaman santai
review_translated_text: Comfortable and relaxing

review_text: Tempatnya persis di SPBU Pejagoan yang dekat sama jembatan sebelum alun-alun Kebumen kalau dari arah barat. Untuk parkir, terutama parkir mobil, tidak begitu luas karena lokasinya yang jadi satu dengan SPBU. Ke sini pas malem minggu ada live music. Kalau dari segi tempat, ada yang indoor, semioutdoor, dan outdoor. Kalau yang outdoor bagus seperti taman-taman. Enaknya kalau di outdoor pas waktu sore/malam dan cuaca cerah. Kalau dari segi makanan, aku pesen nasi goreng teman hati, chicken crispy steak, sama cireng isi ayam. Nasi gorengnya menurutku enak. Chicken steaknya kureng. Cireng isi ayamnya lumayan, cuma sambal cocolannya manis banget jadi berasa dicocolin ke air gula.
review_translated_text: The place is right at the Pejagoan gas station which is close to the bridge before the Kebumen square if you come from the west. Parking, especially car parking, is not very large because the location is one with a gas station. Come here on Sunday evenings and there is live music. In terms of location, there are indoor, semi-outdoor and outdoor. The outdoor ones are nice, like parks. Its nice to be outside in the afternoon/evening and the weather is sunny. In terms of food, I ordered fried rice friend liver, chicken crispy steak, and cireng stuffed with chicken. I think the fried rice is delicious. The chicken steak was dry. The chicken-filled cireng is not bad, but the chili sauce is so sweet that it feels like its been dipped in sugar water.

review_text: Ok sih, pemesanan sesuai waktu yang ditentukan, hanya saja udah pilih paket minum tapi ga dapet minum. Udah ditanyain katanya mau dicek, ternyata sampai pulang ga ada konfirmasi dan akhirnya beli minum lagi terpisah. Rasa kopinya, biasa aja. Untuk pecinta kopi, sepertinya akan kecewa. Cobain mi Laksa rasanya B aja, kebayang creamy rasa kaldu udang ternyata lebih mirip soto santen khas purworejo. Dimsumnya juga ga recommended, kulit alot dan kering banget. Digigit isiannya langsung ambrol. Ga seimbang sama harga. Justru yang enak chicken steak plus dori asam manisnya juaraakk..Worth to buy bangettt. Overall, lumayan lah. Tempat oke, pelayanan ramah. Pilih menu harus pinter2.
review_translated_text: OK, order according to the specified time, its just that I chose the drink package but didnt get a drink. I asked, he said he wanted to check, but when he got home there was no confirmation and he ended up buying another drink separately. The taste of the coffee is just ordinary. For coffee lovers, it looks like you will be disappointed. Try the Laksa noodles, it just tastes B, imagine the creamy taste of shrimp broth, it turns out its more like Purworejos typical coconut milk soto. The dim sum is also not recommended, the skin is tough and very dry. When bitten, the filling immediately collapsed. Not worth the price. In fact, the delicious chicken steak plus sweet and sour dori is a winner... Really worth buying. Overall, its not bad. OK place, friendly service. You have to be smart when selecting menus.

review_text: Eiffel Ice Cream & Resto ini salah satu cafe yang mengusung ice cream sebagai menu utamanya, tapi sayang kemarin ketika berkunjung tidak memesan ice cream nya dan hanya memesan ramen dan jus mangga saja, mungkin komentar ini sesuai dengan selera pribadi. Dengan harga ramen yang bisa dibilang standard yaa itu pula yang kita dapatkan, juga soal minuman bonus atau sepaket dengan ramennya yakni es teh manis, walaupun bisa dikatakan sebagai minuman yang sepaket dengan ramennya, tetapi mungkin rasanya bisa dibuat dengan lebih baik karena menurut selera saya masih lebih enak es teh buatan warung bakso di pasar pasar (kembali lagi sesuai selera), tempat duduk pula yang terbuat dari rotan memang nyaman untuk duduk bersantai, tapi bila digunakan untuk posisi makan rasanya kurang ergonomis karena posisi duduk lebih rendang dari meja, namun yang saya suka dari cafe ini ialah porsi jus yang mendapatkan Refill dan pengemasan dari alat makan customer yang diberi plastik terlebih dahulu menjadi nilai tambah dari cafe ini...
review_translated_text: Eiffel Ice Cream & Resto is one of the cafes that has ice cream as its main menu, but unfortunately when I visited yesterday I didnt order ice cream and only ordered ramen and mango juice, maybe this comment is based on personal taste. With the price of ramen which can be said to be standard, thats what we get, also regarding the bonus drink or package with the ramen, namely sweet iced tea, although it could be said to be a drink that comes with the ramen, but maybe the taste could be made better because according to my taste it is still the iced tea made by the meatball stall at the market is better (again according to taste), the seats are also made of rattan which is comfortable for sitting and relaxing, but when used as a dining position it feels less ergonomic because the sitting position is lower than the table, but what I think What I like about this cafe is that the juice portions get refills and the packaging of customer cutlery which is given plastic first is an added value for this cafe...

review_translated_text: Restaurant in Purworejo which provides various dishes ranging from Ramen, Rice Bowls and other contemporary foods. The prices are affordable and the food is well made and looks attractive. Friendly and good service. Sufficient place to eat, but not too spacious.

This place is suitable for relaxing with friends, or for a surprise birthday event.

review_text: Cukup kecewa dg pelayanan kunjungan hari ini, pernah ke sini pelayanan terkesan menarik dan makanan terbilang enak. Namun hari ini pelayanan cukup mengecewakan, baru datang pelayanan dibagian atas sudah tidak ramah, menu makanan yg diantarakan beberapa kali salah. Minuman diantar setelah menunggu 50 menit, itupun dg bertanya beberapa kali sebelumnya dan sempat diloncati pengunjung yg datang belakangan. Karyawan cukup ketus saat kami ditanyakan kapan makanan datang serta komplain makanan tdk sesuai yg kami pesan, sampau seelsai makan bahkan ada menu yg belum datang. Cukup kecewa dg rasa makanan yg ada, spageti carbonara tdk ada rasanya, nasi goreny asin. Kami cukup paham bila kunjungan rame, namun sebaiknya pengunjung dilayani dg SOP yg seharusnya. Cukup kecewa dan membuat kapok untuk datang lagi... Untuk minuman jg ada kesalahannya, namun masi bisa ditolerir. Namun untuk makanan berat tdk ada rasanya sama sekali, sampai kami meminta tambahan garam seperti di gambar. Walaupun untuk garlc carbonara masih lumayan rasanya, untuk pasta carbonara sangat sedikit dagingnya, dan terlihat sperti pasta instan
review_translated_text: Quite disappointed with the service on todays visit, Ive been here before, the service seemed interesting and the food was delicious. However, today the service was quite disappointing, when we arrived the service at the top was not friendly, the food menu that was served was wrong several times. Drinks were delivered after waiting 50 minutes, even then by asking several times beforehand and being jumped by visitors who came later. The employees were quite annoyed when we asked when the food would come and complained that the food wasnt what we ordered, until after we finished eating, there was even a menu that hadnt arrived. Quite disappointed with the taste of the food, the spaghetti carbonara had no taste, the fried rice was salty. We quite understand if the visit is busy, but visitors should be served with proper SOP. Quite disappointed and discouraged from coming again... There are also mistakes regarding drinks, but they are still tolerable. However, for heavy food there was no taste at all, until we asked for additional salt as in the picture. Although the garlc carbonara still tastes good, the pasta carbonara has very little meat, and looks like instant pasta

review_translated_text: The place for hanging out is good, the drinks are at cafe standard prices. The food is actually affordable, but why not be honest? Order chicken katsu rice (because of Eid the price has increased by 2k, thats okay). But what came was rice with small nugget pieces. The chicken only came in 5 very small pieces. If the menu is rice + nuggets, it should be honestly written on the menu like that. In the menu image it looks like rice + chicken katsu, but in reality? Lots of nuggets. Its a shame, a cafe class like that. Hopefully it will be fixed and can bring in lots of customers

review_text: My current fav kofisyop in Kebumen, untuk kerja sangat kondusif (indoor), wifi dan colokan tersedia. Buat nongki juga enak banget. Minuman dan makanan enak-enak semua. Kopi susunya enak, rasanya balanced, aneka pastrynya pun enak, my fav will be cinnamon roll sama croissant keju nya. Harganya cukup affordable yaa. Untuk makanan ada aneka nasi/spaghetti+chicken karage, sambal bawangnya pedas mantap dan porsi oke banget. Worth it bangeet. All staffs are friendly and helpful. Pelayanan cukup cepat Good job. Fasilitas toilet cukup bersih, mushola mukenanya ga bau dan tempat parkir cukup luas (di timur Cleon). Thumbs up buat Cleon
review_translated_text: My current fav kofisyop in Kebumen, very conducive for work (indoor), wifi and plugs available. Making nongki is also really delicious. Drinks and food are all delicious. The milk coffee is delicious, the taste is balanced, the various pastries are also delicious, my favorite will be the cinnamon roll and the cheese croissant. The price is quite affordable. For food, there are various types of rice/spaghetti+chicken karage, the onion chili sauce is really spicy and the portions are really good. Really worth it. All staffs are friendly and helpful. Service is quite fast. Good job. The toilet facilities are quite clean, the prayer room doesnt smell bad and the parking area is quite spacious (east of Cleon). Thumbs up for Cleon

review_text: Kalau menurut gue, semuanya oke sih ditempat ini. Rasa makanannya enak sesuai lidah saya, harganya affordable, pelayanannya ramah, akan lebih bagus lagi bila bisa dipercepat untuk penyajiannya, atmosfernya pun nyaman. Parkir tersedia cukup luas baik untuk kendaraan roda dua maupun roda empat. Lalu kenapa saya kasih bintang empat? Krn biaya bayar pake QRIS dibebankan kpd  customer. Itu pun sudah dimarkup jadi 1% Biaya QRIS itu menurut aturan dibebankan kpd penjual. Krn yang mendapat keuntungan itu pedagang, ga perlu nyediain kembalian, ga takut uang palsu, ga mudah dimanipulasi kasir dll. Masa bayar 0.3% utk dapat benefit sekian banyak itu ga mau? Ya kalau ga mau ga usah terima pembayaran QRIS, semua serba manual saja. Kalau gue, ada yg begini ini, gue akan bayar cash saja, tapi akan gue kejar seluruh kembaliannya walau 25 perak sekalipun.
review_translated_text: In my opinion, everything is okay here. The taste of the food is delicious according to my taste buds, the price is affordable, the service is friendly, it would be even better if the presentation could be accelerated, the atmosphere is comfortable. Parking is ample for both two-wheeled and four-wheeled vehicles. So why do I give it four stars? Because the cost of paying using QRIS is borne by the customer. That has also been marked up to 1% According to the regulations, QRIS fees are borne by the seller. Because the ones who make the profit are the traders, they dont need to provide change, theyre not afraid of fake money, theyre not easily manipulated by cashiers, etc. Do you want to pay 0.3% to get so many benefits? Yes, if you dont want to, you dont have to accept QRIS payments, its all manual. If it were me, there would be something like this, I would just pay in cash, but I would chase the entire change, even if its 25 silver.

review_text: Pengalaman: Kunjungan ini merupakan kunjungan pertama kami sekeluarga. Kami datang di hari Rabu pukul 11 kurang lebih. Saat itu kami menanyakan, apakah sudah buka, kemudian dijawab sudah. Kami adalah pelanggan pertama yang datang di hari itu. Kami pun masuk dan memilih lantai dua yang lesehan tempatnya. Setelah memilih menu dan menyerahkan ke pramusaji sekitar pukul 11.30 Pukul 12.10 saya turun ke bawah menanyakan mengapa pesanan kami tak juga datang. Ternyata di bawah sudah banyak orang dan di meja mereka sudah ada makanan tersaji. Sementara milik kami satupun belum datang, termasuk minuman. Makanan dan minuman kami datang pukul 12.20. Hampir 1 jam menunggu. Saat sedang menunggu pesanan ada 2 pelanggan datang di sebelah meja kami. Saat kami sedang menghabiskan makanan, pelanggan tsb sudah mendapatkan makanan dan minumannya. Sungguh membuat saya terkejut. Mengapa Kami menunggu hampir 1 jam, sementara pelanggan yg datang baru saja mendapatkan pesanan mereka kurang dari 15 menit? Silahkan disimpulkan sendiri. Makanan: Spaghetti creamy chicken 4/5 Spaghetti spicy alfredo 3/5 (terlalu terasa boncabe nya) Hi Cantik 4,5/5 minuman: Ok Revisit? Dalam waktu dekat sepertinya tidak. Dan keluarga sepertinya juga tidak mau, karena terlalu lama menunggu. Kecewa dengan pelayanan. Karena menurut saya pelayanan belum maksimal. Ada perbedaan dalam pelayanan.
response_from_owner_text: Terima kasih atas kunjungannya kak. Mohon ijin menyampaikan, jam operasional kami jam 12. Kami mohon maaf atas pelayanan yang kurang nyaman. Kami juga berterima kasih ketersediaan kakak untuk menunggu kami prepare hingga kami buka. Ijin menyampaikan, bahwa secara SOP kita operasinal kakak menunggu makanan sekitar 20 menit. Untuk beberapa pelanggan lain yang sudah tersaji lebih dulu, mungkin sudah reservasi via DM/WA ke admin kak. Terima kasih dan mohon maaf sebelumnya atas pelayanan kami saat itu. Kami akan tingkatkan
review_translated_text: Experience: This visit was our first visit as a family. We came on Wednesday at around 11 oclock. At that time we asked whether it was open, then we answered yes. We were the first customers to arrive that day. We went in and chose the second floor where the lesehan was. After choosing the menu and handing it to the waiter at around 11.30 At 12.10 I went downstairs to ask why our order hadnt arrived. It turned out that there were many people downstairs and there was already food being served on their tables. Meanwhile none of ours has yet to arrive, including drinks. Our food and drinks arrived at 12.20. Almost 1 hour waiting. While waiting for our order, 2 customers came next to our table. When we were finishing our food, the customer had already gotten his food and drink. It really surprised me. Why did we wait almost 1 hour, while customers who came in just got their orders in less than 15 minutes? Please conclude for yourself. Food: Spaghetti creamy chicken 4/5 Spaghetti spicy alfredo 3/5 (too much boncabe taste) Hi Beautiful 4.5/5 drink: OK Revisit? Not likely in the near future. And the family doesnt seem to want to either, because it takes too long to wait. Disappointed with service. Because in my opinion the service is not optimal. There are differences in service.
response_from_owner_translated_text: Thank you for your visit sis. Please allow us to convey, our operational hours are 12. We apologize for the uncomfortable service. We also thank you for your availability to wait for us to prepare until we open. Permit said that according to our operational SOP, you wait for food for around 20 minutes. For some other customers who were served earlier, you may have made a reservation via DM/WA to the admin, sis. Thank you and apologize in advance for our service at that time. We will improve

review_translated_text: Im here to order aglio olio pasta.. For me, it just tastes spicy, theres no savory taste, is the aglio olio pasta actually like that or what? I dont really understand, but I think it tastes really spicy.. Then I ordered garlic bread, which I imagine is garlic bread, which is generally like that which is spread on bread and then smeared... In fact, it tastes more like mayonnaise, the garlic texture is really lacking... So when you eat garlic bread, it tastes really bland and sour with mayonnaise...

review_text: Cabang dari UHT Jogja dan memang fokus pada menu-menu western foods. Menu-menunya cukup bervariasi, mulai pasta, salad, sandwich, dll. Pasta dan rice bowlnya cukup enak, tapi panini yang saya pesan tidak sesuai ekspektasi saya. Menurut saya bukan panini, tapi bener-bener kayak roti bakar biasa aja. Semoga diterima ya masukan saya. Sekadar saran, hidden dish yang sering diposting di media sosial UHT menurut saya ga usah di-hide...cantumkan aja di menu. Trus, ada baiknya disediakan tisu di setiap meja, atau sekadar selembar tisu aja di alat makan yang menyertai dish yang dihidangkan. Karena berada di tepi jalan besar yang nyambung ke jalan lingkar, jadi viewnya adalah truk-truk bertonase besar. Unik. Salut dengan keberanian UHT Jogja untuk membuka cabang di Purworejo, karena menu-menu di UHT memang fokus ke western foods dan menurut saya sangat segmented. Semoga sukses, ya!
review_translated_text: A branch of UHT Jogja and focuses on western food menus. The menu is quite varied, from pasta, salads, sandwiches, etc. The pasta and rice bowl were quite delicious, but the panini I ordered did not meet my expectations. I dont think its a panini, but really like ordinary toast. I hope my input is accepted. Just a suggestion, in my opinion the hidden dishes that are often posted on UHT social media dont need to be hidden...just put them on the menu. Then, its a good idea to provide tissue at each table, or just a piece of tissue on the cutlery that accompanies the dish served. Because it is on the edge of a large road that connects to the ring road, the view is of large tonnage trucks. Unique. I salute UHT Jogjas courage to open a branch in Purworejo, because the menu at UHT really focuses on western foods and in my opinion it is very segmented. Good luck!

place_name: HANA CAFE Korean Food, BBQ & Grill
review_text: Resto di kebumen yang menyajikan makanan ala Korea. Terletak dipusat kota kebumen dan mudah dijangkau. Untuk rasa lumayan enak, tergantung selera dari masing masing individu, terlebih bagi pemburu makanan Korea. Fluffy pancakesnya recommended untuk dicoba, sedangkan untuk topoki agak sedikit menyengat/spicy yang terlalu kuat, sehingga untuk yang kurang suka dengan yang pedas tidak disarankan mencoba menu ini. Resto ini juga menyediakan menu paketan (bakaran) dan rebusan ala ala h**am*a, tetapi tidak all u can eat. Untuk suasana juga didesain ala Korea, dengan rekaman musik-musik Korea, tapi sayang untuk yang duduk di luar tidak terdengar. Parkiran untuk beberapa motor dan kalau membawa Mobil cukup sulit karena hanya tersedia hanya 1 saja, tapi Masih bisa parkir didepan atau disebrangnya. Pembayaran hanya menggunakan cash, belum  tersedia mesin EDC. Score : 8/10, RO :Maybe, sikat brayyyy buat yang Pengen coba makanan Korea yang cukup lengkap di kebumen
review_translated_text: Restaurant in Kebumen that serves Korean style food. Located in the center of Kebumen city and easy to reach. As for the taste, its quite good, depending on each individuals taste, especially for Korean food hunters. The fluffy pancakes are recommended to try, while the topoki is a bit overpowering/spicy, so for those who dont like spicy things, it is not recommended to try this menu. This restaurant also provides packaged menus (grilled) and h**am*a style stew, but not all you can eat. The atmosphere is also designed in a Korean style, with recordings of Korean music, but unfortunately for those sitting outside it cant be heard. Parking for several motorbikes and if you bring a car is quite difficult because there is only 1 available, but you can still park in front of or across from it. Payment only using cash, no EDC machine available. Score: 8/10, RO: Maybe, brayyyy for those who want to try Korean food which is quite complete in Kebumen

review_text: Toppokinya enak bangetttttt Minumannya gausah ditanya lah ya emang enak Sayang pelayanan agak lama soalnya yg kerja cuma dua Kasir jd wara wiri nrima pesanan sama nyiapin ini itu Kokinya ada satu jg Cuma ya tempatnya nyaman enak buat nongki Kemaren sambil nunggu pesanan dateng aku ngajak anakku naik permainan hewan yg bisa keliling itu jd ga bosen
review_translated_text: The toppoki is really delicious You dont have to ask about the drink, its really delicious Unfortunately the service took a while because there were only two people working The cashier becomes an expert, taking orders and preparing this and that There is also one chef Its just that the place is comfortable and good for hanging out Yesterday, while waiting for my order to arrive, I took my son on a ride on a moving animal ride so he wouldnt get bored

review_text: Best place ever pelayanannya ramah

review_text: Layanan tunggu pembuatan minumannya terlalu lama, bahkan pelayan mendahulukan orderan berdasar pesanan ukuran tempat minumnya (ukuran minum large lebih dulu dibanding reguler), bukan berdasar nomor antrian. Akibatnya saya menunggu sampai terima minuman dua porsi reguler take away lebih dari 45 menit (hampir satu jam menunggu, selalu didahului orderan yang antriannya setelah saya) sedangkan pengunjung tidak terlalu banyak. Pelayannya tidak ramah karena seperti tidak menerima masukan terlebih ucapkan maaf atas komplain saya. Mengecewakan dan sangat tidak direkomendasikan untuk dikunjungi.
review_translated_text: The waiting service for making drinks takes too long, the waiter even prioritizes orders based on the size of the drink container (large drink sizes come first compared to regular), not based on the queue number. As a result, I waited for more than 45 minutes to receive my regular take away two portion drinks (almost an hour of waiting, always preceded by orders that were queued after me) even though there werent too many visitors. The waiter was not friendly because he didnt seem to accept input, let alone apologize for my complaint. Disappointing and highly not recommended to visit.

review_text: Tempat makan yang cocok kalau bawa anak-anak karena menunya pasti anak suka. Hugo Chicken Bites & Coffee lokasinya ada di dalam Hotel Griya Persada Bandungan. Posisi persis di depan Lobby Hotel. Jadi kalau yg nginap disini sambil nunggu jam check in bisa mampir makan siang dulu. Ayamnya enak kriuknya pas. Pilihan minuman kopinya juga banyak dan enak. Harga pas dikantong mulai dari 25.000 an udah dapet nasi ayam Staff nya juga ramah-ramah. Suasananya nyaman untuk bersantai. Kid-friendliness: Menunya cocok untuk anak-anak
review_translated_text: A suitable place to eat if you bring children because the menu is sure to be liked by children. Hugo Chicken Bites & Coffee is located inside the Griya Persada Hotel Bandungan. Position right in front of the Hotel Lobby. So if you are staying here while waiting for check-in time, you can stop by for lunch first. The chicken is delicious and the crunch is just right. The choice of coffee drinks is also large and delicious. Prices are right for your pocket starting from IDR 25,000 and you get chicken rice The staff is also friendly. The atmosphere is comfortable to relax. Kid-friendliness: The menu is suitable for children

Paket sukinya menarik, murah meriah sudah termasuk suki plus bbq. Pilihan kuah sukinya ada 2, kaldu dan tom yum, keduanya enak. Selain menu suki juga ada menu lainnya. Dari segi kualitas dan rasa, ok banget. Area makan bisa memilih indoor atau outdoor dengan pemandangan asri pedesaan dan gunung Merapi.
review_translated_text: OK, finally there is a Suki restaurant in Boyolali. The location is quite far from the city, towards Madu. The menu offered is quite varied. The suki package is attractive, cheap and includes suki plus bbq. There are 2 choices of suki soup, broth and tom yum, both of which are delicious. Apart from the suki menu, there are also other menus. In terms of quality and taste, its really okay. You can choose the dining area indoor or outdoor with beautiful views of the countryside and Mount Merapi.

review_translated_text: 19agt22. I came here during the day to get excited about writing my thesis while drinking coffee, even though at home there is wifi, coffee, and any snacks, but when Im at home I just want to sleep, hehehe. As usual, if you are looking for a coffee place, you have to look for the signature cake if it is available. Well, this place has cheesecake on Insta but when I got to the location it turned out there wasnt any, I was a bit disappointed because I went there looking for the cake, but it wasnt there. Buy an Ice Americano with pancakes, the coffee and pancakes are delicious. The service is friendly, the digital menu book is good, saves paper, but unfortunately on maps and Insta the menu list is missing, incomplete and not updated. My table was outside the smoking area, it was a bit hot, but I didnt complain because I was looking for quiet to focus because inside the seating arrangement I didnt like because it was too close to the cashier and the seating area was almost close together and there were female customers who would definitely be noisy and chatting excitedly. The wifi is fast. Cant review the situation inside. I dont know if there is background music or not. There are few types of coffee base drinks. Overall OK, no problems. Thank You

review_text: Bintang 3 buat pelayanannya, noted buat Kakak perempuannya. Maaf ya kak, Saya tau mungkin kakak capek, tapi tolong bisa dibedakan perasaannya ya. Kalo soal rasa enak pasti jelas. Pesan di grab yg tinggal ambil jam 11.33. Biar waktunya efisien, karena saya masih ada urusan. Akhirnua waktu pesanan udah siap ambil, langsung ke store, sampe store ternyata pesanan belum dibuat sama sekali tapi ga beralasan. Alias saya harus nunggu dan nanya dulu, baru dikasih tau kalo ternyata cup yg large habis. Itu udah jam 12.05 . oke saya tunggu karyawannha beli cup. Cukup lama, sampe akhirnya ada costumer lain yg nanya juga buat pesanan tinggal ambil yg via grab. Tapi bedanya, costumer lain ditawarkan 1 cup largenya diganti dengan 2 cup medium. kenapa saya tidak? . Beberapa kali saya nanya juga karyawan ga berani langsung menjawab menghadap saya, malah bicara dengan memunggungi saya. sudah dibuat menunggu dengan ketidak jelasan, pun ditambah sikap karyawan yg begini. Setelah cup yg large datang, pesanan saya pun ga segera dibuat, malah costumer yg dine in atau yg datang dan pesan langsung yg dibuat. Sebenernya kalo saya disuruh nunggu, masih ga papa kak, tapi tolong diperhatikan lagi urutan pesanannya, dan coba tolong berani menghadap ke yg berbicara. Akhirnya pesanan saya selesai jam 12.35 . 1 jam dari saya pesan . Kalo tadi saya dikasih penjelasan yg jelas saya masih terima kok kak. Maaf ya kak, makasihh. Semangat kerjanya kak, semoga tidak ada costumer lain yang diperlakukan seperti itu lagi. Have a great day
review_translated_text: 3 stars for the service, noted for his sister. Im sorry sis, I know you might be tired, but please differentiate your feelings. If its about good taste, its clear. Order on grab which only needs to be picked up at 11.33. So that my time is efficient, because I still have things to do. Finally, when the order was ready to be picked up, we went straight to the store, when we arrived at the store it turned out that the order had not been made at all but that was no excuse. Aka I have to wait and ask first, then Ill be told if the large cup is out of stock. It was already 12.05. OK, Ill wait for the employee to buy a cup. It took quite a while, until finally another customer asked for an order, just take it via Grab. But the difference is, other customers are offered 1 large cup replaced with 2 medium cups. why not me? . Several times I asked questions and the employees didnt dare answer directly facing me, instead talking with their backs to me. Ive been made to wait with uncertainty, plus the employees attitude is like this. After the large cup arrived, my order wasnt made immediately, instead customers who came in or came and ordered it were made straight away. Actually, if I was told to wait, it would still be okay, sis, but please pay attention to the order of the order, and try to have the courage to face the person speaking. Finally my order was completed at 12.35. 1 hour after I ordered . If I had been given a clear explanation, I would still have accepted it, sis. Sorry, sis, thank you. Good luck with your work, I hope no other customer will be treated like that again. Have a great day

Minuman yang belakangan ini sangat diganderungi oleh kaum millenial adalah salah satu pelopor franchise Thai Tea Street di Indonesia. Berdiri sejak tahun 2015, kini Fremilt tersebar ratusan outlet di berbagai kota di seluruh Indonesia.
review_translated_text: Uke Fremilt itself is a tea drink mixed with coffee and milk which comes from a typical drink from Thailand. A drink that has recently been very popular with millennials is one of the pioneers of the Thai Tea Street franchise in Indonesia. Founded in 2015, Fremilt now has hundreds of outlets in various cities throughout Indonesia.

The order process until the food is delivered to the table also doesnt take long. review_text: Dialogue Bar & Bistro lokasinya ada di dalam Hotel Griya Persada Bandungan. Tidak perlu menginap jika ingin kesini, terbuka untuk umum. Tempatnya oke, nyaman untuk nongkrong. Terkadang ada event live music dan DJ. Ada meja bilyardnya juga disini. Staffnya ramah dan keren2. Makanannya enak, minumannya juga banyak pilihannya. Harga terjangkau. Sangat direkomendasikan.
review_translated_text: Dialogue Bar & Bistro is located inside the Griya Persada Hotel Bandungan. No need to stay overnight if you want to come here, it is open to the public. The place is okay, comfortable for hanging out. Sometimes there are live music and DJ events. There is a pool table here too. The staff are friendly and cool. The food is delicious, there are also many choices of drinks. Affordable prices. Highly recommended.

review_text: Recommended! Salah satu cafe(?) yang nyaman buat hangout. Letaknya samping jalan kecil tapi ngga bising. Pelayannya ramah dan tempatnya lumayan bersih. Makanannya enak!! Pesan bento nasi dan kentang. Salad disajikan fresh, selada sama tomatnya segar dan manis, dressing saladnya juga enak. Ayamnya enak, kripsi tapi lembut dan disajikan fresh masih panas. Saus asam manis yang dituang di ayamnya enak, ada bawang bombay+ditaburi wijen. Untuk bento bisa pilih pakai nasi/kentang/mie/salad. Porsinya nasi dan kentang ngga pelit. Roti bakar mix rasanya standar tapi tetep enak. Es teh lumayan enak. Minusnya, penyajian lumayan lama sekitar 30 menit-an. Parkir tidak berbayar dan buka pagi jam 10. Overall nice place to hang out
review_translated_text: Recommended! One of the cafes(?) that is comfortable for hanging out. Its located next to a small road but its not noisy. The waiters are friendly and the place is quite clean. The food is delicious!! Order a rice and potato bento. The salad is served fresh, the lettuce and tomatoes are fresh and sweet, the salad dressing is also delicious. The chicken is delicious, crispy but soft and served fresh, still hot. The sweet and sour sauce poured on the chicken is delicious, there are onions + sprinkled with sesame. For bento, you can choose to use rice/potatoes/noodles/salad. The portions of rice and potatoes are not stingy. Mixed toast tastes standard but still delicious. The iced tea is pretty good. The downside is that the serving takes quite a long time, around 30 minutes. Parking is free and opens at 10am. Overall nice place to hang out

review_text: Tadi cobain creme brulle latte dan ternyata light dan creamy. Pas pemesanan mbaknya nanya dulu, mau yg strong kopinya atau biasa aja? Untuk rasa kopi yg lebih kuat, kalian bisa pesan double shot. Pesanan lainnya adalah choco mint. Salah satu choco mint yg mendefinisikan mint itu sendiri. Its end, nambah 1 gelas lagi untuk minuman ini. Sementara, untuk minuman, cocok sama cetroo ini. Pertahankan terus, please. Kekurangan? Untuk lokasi yg lumayan nyaman dengan pemandangan langsung ke alun-alun sebenernya lebih seru lagi kalau ada makanan2 ringan yg yummy kaya sandwich, frenchfries, cookies, brownies. Kalau bisa ada menu kaya ricebowl juga... Well, karena tadi laper banget dan saffron resto (masih 1 area) sudah tutup, terpaksa pesan nasi goreng dr luar.. Tapi untuk minumannya, kayanya bakal balik kesini lagi..
review_translated_text: I tried the creme brulle latte earlier and it turned out light and creamy. When ordering, Miss asked first, do you want strong coffee or just regular coffee? Because it was already late, so I ordered a light, aka 1 shot of espresso. The combination of 1 shot of espresso and milk (fresh milk diamond) is just right in my opinion. Still a balance between the taste of milk and coffee. For a stronger coffee taste, you can order a double shot. Another order is choco mint. One of the choco mints that defines mint itself. Its end, add 1 more glass to this drink. Meanwhile, for drinks, this cetroo is suitable. Keep it up, please. Lack? For a fairly comfortable location with a direct view of the square, its actually even more exciting if there are yummy snacks like sandwiches, French fries, cookies, brownies. If possible there is a menu like rice bowl too... Well, because I was really hungry and the saffron restaurant (only one area) was closed, I had to order fried rice from outside... But for the drinks, I think Ill come back here again...

Of course, for those of you who love coffee, there are also quite a lot of options available. There is free Wi-Fi, a prayer room and fairly clean toilets. The parking area for motorbikes can accommodate quite a lot, but for 4-wheelers you have to park on the side of the road.

Prices are relatively cheap (compared to Semarang city where the prices are unreasonable for local tourists like me). Hopefully I can come here again next time

review_translated_text: A place to eat and relax with aesthetic decoration Beautiful comfortable atmosphere Spacious place There are ancient decorations Good service Food for the buffet, a complete menu of various Javanese dishes If you have the option to drink various coffees, there is one Ample parking

review_text: Tempatnya yang berada di tengah kota dan mudah dijangkau dengan suasana dan vibes yang tenang. Menu makanan prasmanannya beragam, nasinya pun terdiri dari nasi putih, masi merah, nasi kuning dan bubur lemu. Pengunjung bisa menyesuaikan nasi dan lauk mereka. Pun dengan minuman dan ragam snacknya. Disini saya pesan es beras kencur, segar. Dari segi harga, termasuk murah yaa~~~
review_translated_text: The place is in the middle of the city and easy to reach with a calm atmosphere and vibes. The buffet menu is varied, the rice also consists of white rice, red rice, yellow rice and lemu porridge. Diners can customize their rice and side dishes. Even with drinks and various snacks. Here I ordered iced rice kencur, fresh. In terms of price, its cheap~~~

review_text: Makanan enak. Pelayanan ramah. Bersih. Ada 3 pilihan nasi. Bubur, nasi kuning, dan nasi putih. Semuanya pokwe (jipuk dewe/ ambil sendiri)    Pagi sudah buka, jadi bisa sarapan di sini kalau lewat boyolali
review_translated_text: Delicious food. Friendly service. Clean. There are 3 choices of rice. Porridge, yellow rice and white rice. Everything is pokwe (jipuk dewe/pick it up yourself)    Its already open in the morning, so you can have breakfast here if youre passing through Boyolali

review_text: Kesan pertama masuk tempat ini benar benar terasa adem, asri, meyenangkan dan berasa rumah. Walaupun saat kesini sedang ramai ramainya tapi tetap nyaman. Pelayanan sangat baik, suasana sangaaat baik, dan makanannya juga enak. Makanan rumahan dengan pilihan lauk yang banyak. Sangat berkesan dengan suasana dan pelayanan disini. Wajib mampir kalau lewat yaa!!
review_translated_text: The first impression of entering this place is that it really feels cool, beautiful, fun and feels like home. Even though its busy here, its still comfortable. The service is very good, the atmosphere is very good, and the food is also delicious. Home-cooked food with a large choice of side dishes. Very impressed with the atmosphere and service here. You have to stop by if youre passing by!!

review_text: Cafe for heavy meals with a complete home menu Recommended side dishes, the tea is really delicious The service is good, friendly and the atmosphere is definitely Javanese, relaxed, romantic and lots of photo spots

review_translated_text: The food is delicious and the menu is quite complete Carrying the concept of traditional Javanese cuisine The drinks are also varied Affordable prices The traditional atmosphere is thicker with the pyramid-shaped restaurant building Parking is quite spacious and safe

review_translated_text: Nice

review_text: Tempatnya nyaman utk santai berlama2 dsana,cuma harga makanan dan minumannya terlalu mahal tdk sebanding dengan rasa makanan yg d sajikan
review_translated_text: The place is comfortable to relax and spend time there, but the price of food and drinks is too expensive, not comparable to the taste of the food served

review_text: warung makan yang nuansanya anti-design classic, wkwk. apa apa barang di masa jadoel pasti ada, tv, radio, kltokkan, sampe iklan indomie, pepsodent, dan rinso jadul pun ada semua diletakan secara menyebar tanpa ada klasifikasi tertentu, tapi justru itu kek ngasih tour ke jaman jadul. rasa-rasanya kalau bisa ada tour guidenya kita bisa ditarik ke nuansa masa lalu sambil cerita satu-persatu tentang benda apa itu yang dipajang. makanan mantab, banyak opsi, cuman kalo malam kudu siap siap terima apa adanya karena sering habis. paling fav si mangut ikannya, mangut abis, ndak terlalu pedas, sama tidak amis. cocok banget dimakan sama nasi hangat. fasilitas kumplit, bersih, parkir sedikit sempit tapi ada opsi ditaroh di halaman belakang, yang disayangkan speaker buat nyetel music ndempet banget sama mushola, jadi kalau sholat kedengeran musiknya, malah yang dibelakang malah ndak kedengaran apa-apa. overall mantab si buat suasana, rasa, dan fasilitas yang di dapat. buat harga, standard aja. Parking: dipinggir jalan agak susah, tapi ada parkiran di belakang warung yang cukup luas buat beberapa mobil.
review_translated_text: a food stall that has an anti-classic design feel, hahaha. There are certainly items from the old era, TV, radio, kltokkan, even old school Indomie, Pepsodent and Rinso advertisements, all of which are placed scattered without any particular classification, but in fact its like giving a tour of the old school era. I think if there could be a tour guide, we could be drawn into the nuances of the past while telling stories one by one about what objects are on display. great food, lots of choices, but at night you have to be prepared to accept what is because it often runs out. My favorite is the fish bite, its really delicious, not too spicy, not fishy either. Very suitable to eat with warm rice. complete facilities, clean, parking is a little tight but there is an option to put it in the back yard, whats unfortunate is that the speakers for playing music are really close to the prayer room, so when you pray you hear the music, even those behind you dont hear anything. Overall its great for the atmosphere, taste and facilities you get. For prices, just standard. Parking: The side of the road is a bit difficult, but there is parking behind the shop which is large enough for several cars.

review_text: Pertama kali datang kesini pas momen setelah lebaran, meja hampir semuanya penuh, parkir mobil ada di belakang resto, paling hanya muat 10 mobil, resto dengan konsep prasmanan masakan khas jawa, yang ingin nostalgia masakan neneknya waktu kecil seperti plecing, terik tempe, bobor, lodeh jantung pisang, cocok sekali kesini, cuma sayang tidak ada pelayan yang standby di lokasi prasmanan jadi tidak bisa tanya-tanya nama masakan nya, untuk pelayanan cukup cepat, rasa masakan juga enak, suasana seperti di rumah jawa jaman dulu
review_translated_text: The first time I came here was right after Eid, the tables were almost all full, the car park was behind the restaurant, at most it could only fit 10 cars, the restaurant had a typical Javanese buffet concept, for those who wanted nostalgia for their grandmothers cooking when they were little, such as plecing, terik tempe, bobor, banana flower lodeh, very suitable here, its just a shame there are no waiters on standby at the buffet location so you cant ask about the name of the dish, the service is quite fast, the taste of the food is also delicious, the atmosphere is like in an old Javanese house

review_text: Ada prasmanan nya , memang agak di sudut2 tapi ada tandanya , kalo yang pake mobil parkirnya di seberang soalnya sempit buat mobil parkir di depan kafenya , makanan nya enak2 dan juga minuman nya , ada free wifi juga 5G , password nya ada di pajangan2 di belakang kasir , menurut aku parkir mobilnya harus di perbesar sih Parking: Parkirnya sempit buat mobil , kalo motor sih muat2 aja , parkiran buat mobil ada di toko seberang kafe nya
review_translated_text: There is a buffet, its a bit in a corner but there is a sign, if youre using a car, park opposite because its narrow for cars to park in front of the cafe, the food is delicious and the drinks are delicious, theres free wifi and 5G, the password is on the display behind the cashier , I think the car park should be enlarged Parking: The parking lot is tight for cars, if you can only fit a motorbike, parking for cars is in the shop opposite the cafe.

review_text: Salah satu tempat yang paling direkomendasikan saat berkunjung di Purworejo. Sajian makanan dan minuman yang jarang ditemui ditempat lain. Saat tempat lain menyajikan berbagai biji kopi arabika dari berbagai daerah, kedai ini menyediakan biji kopi robusta hasil panen petani lokal. Selain kopi banyak variasi minuman yang bisa jadi pilihan. Berbagai makanan juga dapat dijadikan teman nimum kopi yang pastinya semuanya dengan harga terjangkau. Tempatnya luas, tidak bising oleh kendaraan maupun pengunjung yang berteriak main game. Sangat cocok untuk membawa serta keluarga, namun kurangnya ketersediaan lahan parkir membuat banyak kendaraan memakai bahu jalan.
response_from_owner_text: Terima kasih
review_translated_text: One of the most recommended places when visiting Purworejo. Food and drink offerings that are rarely found elsewhere. While other places serve various Arabica coffee beans from various regions, this shop provides Robusta coffee beans harvested by local farmers. Apart from coffee, there are many variations of drinks that you can choose from. Various foods can also be used as companions for drinking coffee, all of which are at affordable prices. The place is spacious, there is no noise from vehicles or visitors shouting to play games. It is very suitable for bringing the family along, but the lack of available parking means many vehicles use the shoulder of the road.
response_from_owner_translated_text: Thank You

Ever since I moved to this city, this cafe has become my go-to spot for hanging out with family or getting some work done. Out of all the cafes Ive tried in town, this place stands out with its unbeatable coffee, both in terms of taste and price. The cozy and welcoming ambiance makes it the perfect spot to unwind, especially since theyve recently moved to a brand new building. Not to mention, the Wi-Fi is super fast and reliable, which is a huge plus for me. The staff is always friendly and attentive, providing excellent service, although there might be a slight delay during peak hours. Their menu offers a variety of delicious food options, ranging from quick snacks like toast, burgers, and fries to satisfying meals like Nasi Goreng and Ayam Geprek, all at an incredibly friendly price less than IDR 25K. Personally, I cant get enough of their Nasi Goreng Katsu and their refreshing Japanese iced coffee. Overall, I highly recommend this cafe to anyone in search of a fantastic coffee experience in a comfortable setting. Whether youre catching up with friends, enjoying a family dinner, or focusing on work, this place is definitely worth a visit.

Lha trus d jwb iya...mba nya smbil ngmong sma temenya tu kan .. di bilangin juga...dstu rsnya kesel bngt sih..brty dr td ngga d bkin itu pesenan...pdhl karyawan banyakk...memang pssinya rame bngtt...tpi kan kta dah reservasi dr pagii...bukan yg dateng dadakan... Memang terbilang murah ya...tisuuu gaadaa...itu aku smpe bawa tisu sendiri...kipas angin juga d tmpat aku duduk itu ngga ada..adanya yg d dalem ruangan sebelah aku dduk...kurang nyaman juga krna kaya dduk d atas dipan gitu bukan dpt yg lesehan sklian ... Cukup sihh sekali ajah...ngga lagii...
review_translated_text: 6/4/2024...exactly last Sunday evening...my friend made a reservation from 10 noon... Intention to make bukber...ordered grilled tilapia...mineral water...fruit soup..sma iced tea..chocolate milkshake...when we got there grilled tilapia with rice + fresh vegetables..ice tea with mineral water..it was ready. ..the grilled tilapia has a dominant sweet taste.. but its wrong... ordered 2 iced teas... and then 3... in the end, I returned it... asked for fruit soup and milk shakes because they werent there yet.. the male waiter... then he told me to wait... okay... I waited until I finished eating... why didnt you come... asked again... the fruit soup was said to be empty... the waiter was a girl... told me to change the menu, I didnt want to... finally got my money back... because when I made the reservation it was already there. byr y right...I asked about the milk shake...it said I was waiting for it to be made...5 times my high school friend changed and just asked for the milk shake...until the last time my friend was annoyed he said...so Is the milk shake coming out?... Well, then he answered yes... his mother said while talking to her friend thats right... she told me that too... then the hospital was really upset... so since then she didnt make the order... even though there were a lot of employees... Its certainly very busy... but we made a reservation early in the morning... not those who came suddenly... Its really cheap... theres no tissue... I even brought my own tissue... theres no fan where Im sitting... theres one in the room next to me sitting... its also not comfortable because its like sitting On a couch like that, you cant even get a seat on the couch... Just once is enough...no more...

review_text: Kami coba karena review google yang cukup baik dengan skor hampir 5.0 Kami berkunjung pada 13 Marey 2023 tiba sekitar pk. 17.00 Penilaian kami, Restoran ini menyajikan makanan dan minuman dengan harga masih cukup terjangkau untuk kalangan menengah ke bawah dan masih sesuai untuk kalangan menengah namun dengan harga ekonomis. Bakmi rebusnya cukup enak dengan porsi yang luar biasa banyak, Kalau orang normal dan manis seperti saya dan bukan orang bar-bar, semangkuk bisa untuk berdua. Istri saya tidak habis karena kepedasan meski order pedas sedang. Ya, istri saya cupu pedas, tapi untuk saya mana dan saya katakan menu ini cukup enak. Sop buntutnya cukup enak, rempah dan masam jeruknya juga berasa. Menu ini cukup saya rekomendasikan dan perlu Anda coba. Original steak ala Boyolali, sekitar 200 gram,  harga Rp. 50 ribuan, bagi saya cukup rasa dan tata cara penyajian cukup baik. Mungkin karena lupa order kematangannya jadi dimasak welldone, sehingga untuk bapak-bapak seperti saya, saya merasa daging agak keras, mungkin bila kematangan medium akan lebih lunak dan juicy bila bisa dicustom. Namun jangan khawatir, saucenya cukup enak dan steak tadi masih sangat bisa dinikmati. Mungkin bisa dikembangkan lebih lanjut ke depan, pengunjung bisa ditawarkan tingkat kematangannya. Menu lain-lain cukup enak kelas ala-ala makanan kafe mahasiswa cukup duit. Untuk minumnya, rata-rata standar dan cukup baik. Hanya saya order es beras kencur, saya rasa terlalu ringan dan kurang kental, mungkin bisa dievaluasi. Varian menu cukup banyak. Namun hati-hati ketika mencoba beberapa menu, karena bisa tabrakan rasa. Suasana juga cukup baik, termaram, tidak terlalu ramai ketika kami berkunjung. Kami merasa masih sangat cukup nyaman meskipun ada bagian yang remang-remang, bisa di siasati untuk duduk di area yang dekat jendela. Pemandangan area Pasar Sunggingan dan kawasan boyolali membuat kami merasa adem. Akses kursi roda masih bisa disiasati secara mudah meskipun ada bagian berundak karena tidak terlalu tinggi. Lokasi, Anda bisa lihat sendiri, resto ini berada di area pusat ekonomi Kota Boyolali. Untuk pelayanan, Seorang pegawai laki-laki yang mendatangi kami di awal sangat menguasai detail menu dengan sangat baik dan ketika berganti orang, sang pengganti hampir tidak menguasai detail menu. Namun bukan masalah mayor, pemilik/ pengelola bisa melakukan sedikit pembinaan/ pelatihan lagi supaya pegawai lebih baik lagi. Waktu tunggu sajian juga tidak terlalu lama. Kesimpulan kami, Restoran ini 1. Menyajikan makanan yang cukup baik dan enak. 2. Memiliki harga makanan dan minuman cukup terjangkau, juga untuk menengah ke bawah. 3. Memiliki suasana cukup baik dan nyaman. 4. Memiliki akses yang masih ramah untuk difabel. 5. Memiliki pelayanan masih cukup baik. 6. Lokasi di tengah kota. 7. Ada sedikit kekurangan minor yang sangat wajar dan bisa diperbaiki pengelola/ pemilik. Saran kami, 1. Untuk masyarakat, Anda bisa memilih restoran ini ssbagai salah satu pilihan atau tempat makan di tengah Kota Boyolali. 2. Untuk pemilik/ pengelola, semoga tetap selalu bisa menjaga kualitas menu dan pelayanan. Doa kami semoga semakin baik dan berkembang, menjadi berkat dan pilihan bagi masyarakat. Salam hormat untuk semua, Tuhan memberkati. Kid-friendliness: Umumnya menu tidak pedas, hanya sedikit menu yang pedas. Request pedas sangat memungkinkan Wheelchair accessibility: Masih mudah dijangkau
review_translated_text: We tried it because the Google reviews were quite good with a score of almost 5.0 We visited on March 13, 2023 arriving around 10 p.m. 17.00 Our assessment, This restaurant serves food and drinks at prices that are still quite affordable for the lower middle class and still suitable for the middle class but at economical prices. The boiled noodles are quite delicious with an extraordinarily large portion. If you are a normal and sweet person like me and not a bar person, a bowl can serve two people. My wife didnt finish because of the spiciness even though she ordered medium spicy. Yes, my wifes cupu is spicy, but thats fine for me and I say this menu is quite delicious. The oxtail soup is quite delicious, the spices and sour orange also taste good. I really recommend this menu and you need to try it. Original Boyolali style steak, around 200 grams, price Rp. 50 thousand, for me the taste and serving method are quite good. Maybe because I forgot to order the doneness so it was cooked well done, so for men like me, I feel the meat is a bit tough, maybe if it is medium done it will be softer and juicier if you can customize it. But dont worry, the sauce is quite delicious and the steak can still be enjoyed. Maybe it can be developed further in the future, visitors can be offered levels of maturity. The other menus are quite delicious, student cafe style food, enough money. As for the drink, its average and quite good. I only ordered iced rice kencur, I felt it was too light and not thick enough, maybe it could be evaluated. There are quite a lot of menu variations. However, be careful when trying several menus, because the taste can clash. The atmosphere is also quite good, dim, not too busy when we visited. We felt it was still quite comfortable even though there were parts that were dimly lit, we could get around sitting in the area near the window. The view of the Sunggingan Market area and the Boyolali area made us feel cool. Wheelchair access can still be easily accessed even though there are steps because it is not too high. Location, you can see for yourself, this restaurant is in the economic center area of Boyolali City. For service, A male employee who came to us at the beginning mastered the menu details very well and when he changed people, the replacement barely mastered the menu details. But its not a major problem, the owner/manager can do a little more coaching/training so that the employees are better. The waiting time for food is also not too long. Our conclusion, This restaurant 1. Serves food that is quite good and tasty. 2. Food and drink prices are quite affordable, also for the lower middle class. 3. Has a fairly good and comfortable atmosphere. 4. Has access that is still friendly for people with disabilities. 5. The service is still quite good. 6. Location in the city center. 7. There are a few minor deficiencies which are very normal and can be corrected by the manager/owner. Our suggestion, 1. For the community, you can choose this restaurant as one of the choices or places to eat in the middle of Boyolali City. 2. For the owner/manager, hopefully they can always maintain the quality of the menu and service. We pray that it will get better and develop, becoming a blessing and choice for the community. Greetings to all, God bless. Kid-friendliness: Generally the menu is not spicy, only a few menus are spicy. Spicy requests are very possible Wheelchair accessibility: Still easy to reach

Ini agak bikin jengkel sih karena bener2 gelap2an disana dan ga ada yg ngasi tau kalau listrik disana konslet sampai aku nanya ke bar Tp buat pelayanan, okey semuanya. Mba dan mas ramah semua, makanan enak, kopi enak, tempat nyaman. Saran: ada kanopi buat parkiran motor, kasih spot colokan di area depan bar yg mepet ruang ac, dan lebih aware juga sama pelanggan. But maybe ill come back again, semoga segalanya sudah jadi lebih baik yaaa
review_translated_text: This has been changed to a coffee jacket, thats the place. Came here when it was still soft opening and it was a bit chaotic 1. Came in the afternoon after heavy rain, looked for a good spot to work on the laptop, found it in front of the bathroom. The tables and chairs used for water baths were not wiped or offered to be wiped. 2. Ordered 3 additional menus 1 hour apart there, forgot to deliver 1 drink. 3. Towards sunset, the lights werent turned on, so I asked the staff. He said it was a short circuit. This was a bit annoying because it was really dark there and no one told me there was a short circuit until I asked at the bar But for service, everything is okay. Maam and bro are all friendly, delicious food, delicious coffee, comfortable place. Suggestions: have a canopy for parking motorbikes, provide plug spots in the area in front of the bar which is close to the AC space, and be more aware of customers. But maybe Ill come back again, hopefully everything will be better

I was surprised too I ordered the Blackpaper flavor, thank God it was delicious. Minuses: RAW POTATOES!! Hard and not pleasant to eat. We all know that potatoes must be cooked for a long time to make them soft. These seem to only cook for 2-3 minutes in a stir frying pan. And the potatoes arent boiled like that.
