review_text: Mau cerita, ini tentang permohonan maaf sebagai customer. Makan di sini dengan 2 org sahabatku. Waktu itu salah satu temen kita ultah, terus minta sesuatu (apa aja) yg penting atasnya dikasih tulisan HBD. Terus yang keluar roti bakar dengan tulisan HBD dari susu dan keju di atasnya dan sahabat saya spontan bilang ih gini doang gak modal banget. Aku gak tau Mas/Mba pramusaji denger atau enggak cuman sahabat aku itu ngomongnya lumayan keras. Gara2 itu jujur saya sebagai customer merasa sahabat saya ini gak menghargai yang bikin makanan. Padahal menurutku yang bikin pasti sudah sangat effort sekali, apalagi sahabatku minta seperti ini dadakan dan situasi cafe masih rame banget. Bikin seperti ini tentu butuh waktu kan ya Mas/Mba? Makasih banget dan tolong maklumin sahabat saya ya Mas/Mba, dia belum paham hecticnya kerja di perdapuran seperti apa. Padahal menurut aku pribadi cafe ini sangat cepat sekali dalam menyajikan makanan padahal waktu itu pas lagi rame banget. Semoga sukses terus ya untuk owner dan kru yg terlibat termasuk pak2 parkir yang baik hati.
review_translated_text: I want to tell you, this is about apologizing as a customer. Ate here with 2 of my friends. At that time, one of our friends had a birthday, and he asked for something (anything) important and he was given the words HBD. Then toast came out with the words HBD made of milk and cheese on it and my best friend spontaneously said, Oh, its not like thats really capital. I dont know if the waiter heard you or not, but my best friend was talking quite loudly. Because of that, honestly, as a customer, I feel that my friend doesnt respect those who make the food. In fact, in my opinion, those who made it must have put a lot of effort into it, especially since my friend asked for it like this suddenly and the cafe was still very busy. Making something like this certainly takes time, right sir/madam? Thank you very much and please explain to my friend, sir/madam, that he doesnt understand what its like to work in a kitchen. Even though I personally think this cafe is very fast in serving food even though its really busy at that time. Good luck to the owner and crew involved, including the kind parking crew.

review_text: Berwisata ke alun-alun Bandungan dan mencari tempat untuk makan malam dan mampir ke resto ini. Kelihatannya sepi tapi setelah mencari-cari informasi ternyata tempat ini adalah resto legendaris di Bandungan. Dari menu yang kami pilih, ayam goreng serundengnya cukup menculik perhatian kami sekeluarga. Gurihnya ayam berpadu sempurna dengan gurih manisnya serundeng. Nasi goreng jawa juga lumayan enak, tapi sayang terlalu manis untuk saya, mungkin kecap manisnya bisa dikurangi. Interiornya yang jadul dan sejuknya Bandungan memang pas banget. Lokasinya juga strategis, selesai makan tinggal menyeberang ke alun-alun Bandungan. Tempat parkirnya juga cukup lega, bisa untuk 3-4 mobil.
response_from_owner_text: Trimakasih banyak Pak Paulus, sudah mampir, trimakasih juga ulasan dan bintang 5 nya.....
review_translated_text: Traveled to Bandungan square and looked for a place to have dinner and stopped by this restaurant. It looks quiet but after searching for information it turns out that this place is a legendary restaurant in Bandungan. From the menu we chose, the fried chicken serundeng was enough to capture our familys attention. The savory taste of the chicken combines perfectly with the sweet and savory serundeng. Javanese fried rice is also quite delicious, but unfortunately its too sweet for me, maybe the sweet soy sauce can be reduced. The old school interior and the coolness of Bandungan are really fitting. The location is also strategic, after eating, just cross to Bandungan square. The parking space is also quite spacious, enough for 3-4 cars.
response_from_owner_translated_text: Thank you very much Mr Paul, for stopping by, thank you for the review and 5 stars.....

review_text: Makan Chinese food yg ga mahal, banyak banget pilihan menu nya, rasa juga oke. Suka bingung kalau di Bandungan bermalam, mau makan apa kalau bersama keluarga, bisa jadi kan depot ini salah satu pilihan. Halal yah. Ukuran menu ga terlalu besar. Tempat parkir ga banyak jadi ikuti arahan tukang parkir. Pembayaran kemarin hanya bisa tunai. Toilet sign nya ga gitu jelas tapi ada di sisi kanan dari kasir. Rekomendasi menu buat dipesan: - cumi goreng saus inggris - Nasi goreng yangzhou - Mie goreng - Ikan gurami juga fresh Parking: Ikuti arahan tukang parkir. Ga boleh parkir di depot sebelah juga. Wheelchair accessibility: Ngga ada akses khusus, harus drop di depan baru cari parkir.
review_translated_text: Eat Chinese food which is not expensive, there are lots of menu choices, the taste is also good. If you are confused when you spend the night in Bandungan, what to eat with your family, this depot could be an option. Its halal, okay? The menu size is not too big. There are not many parking spaces so follow the parking attendants directions. Yesterdays payment was only cash. The toilet sign is not very clear but it is on the right side of the cashier. Menu recommendations to order: - fried squid in English sauce - Yangzhou fried rice - Fried noodles - Gourami fish is also fresh Parking: Follow the parking attendants directions. You cant park at the depot next door either. Wheelchair accessibility: There is no special access, you have to drop off at the front to find parking.

Kedua kali ada mie, anak anak saya pesankan mie dengan catatan tidak pedas, tapi mungkin memang bumbunya sudah diracik dengan rasa pedas,  jadi mie yang tersaji rasanya pedas. Mungkin untuk yang ngajak anak anak yang belum bisa makan pedas, lebih baik pesan menu sambal gami yang pisah saja, jangan pesan mie. Parking: Tempat parkir luas, tapi ketika saya ke sana dua kali tidak ada tukang parkir, jadi perlu parkir sendiri dan gratis Kid-friendliness: Sambal gami pisah bisa jadi alternatif untuk anak yang tidak suka pedas.
review_translated_text: First, go to Sambal Gami, try the skin and shrimp sambal gami menu, the kids love it, the chili sauce can be separated so the kids can eat. Coincidentally, when I wanted to order noodles, the supply ran out. The second time there were noodles, my children ordered noodles with the note that they werent spicy, but maybe the seasoning had been mixed with a spicy taste, so the noodles served tasted spicy. Maybe for those who invite children who cant eat spicy food, its better to just order a separate menu of chili gamis, dont order noodles. Parking: The parking lot is large, but when I went there twice there was no parking attendant, so you need to park yourself and its free Kid-friendliness: Separate gami chili sauce can be an alternative for children who dont like spicy food.

review_text: Kesini pesen kepiting. Per porsi harga 160.000 . Pas makan kaget loh ges. Daging kepiting nya masih fresh. Kalo udah di frozen daging kepiting bakal punya tekstur ga lembut dan agak aneh di makan. Ga jarang juga amis. Kalo fresh jauh lebih lembut dan manis. Aku juga beli bakmi nya. Enakkkk... Kayaknya bapaknya ni pernah kerja di resto apa yaaa..hehhe. Aku liat pas masak bakmi langsung bikin porsi besar. Ga gampang buat masak sekali dengan porsi besar. Karna takaran bumbunya bisa berubah. Porsinya juga gede.. Bener enak loh. Ga berasa makan makanan warung pinggir jalan loh. Worth it to buy. Minus nya cuma satu, karna warung nya di pinggir jalan. Dan kebetulan yah jalanannya jadi salah satu jalan utama yg sering di lewatin wisatawan dan warga lokal. Jadi bising nya minta ampun. Hey.. Heyy satu lagi. KALO KESINI DATANGNYA SORE AJA. KALO ABIS MAGHRIB WAH SIAP SIAP SABAR YAA NUNGGU LAMA. ANTRI SOALNYA HEHEHEHEHE.
review_translated_text: Come here and order crab. Per portion price 160,000. When you eat, youre shocked. The crab meat is still fresh. If the crab meat has been frozen, it will not have a soft texture and be a bit strange to eat. Its not uncommon to be fishy either. If its fresh, its much softer and sweeter. I also bought the noodles. Thats delicious... I think his father once worked at a restaurant... hehhe. I saw that when I cook noodles, I immediately make a big portion. Its not easy to cook a large portion. Because the spice dosage can change. The portion is also big... Its really delicious. It doesnt feel like eating roadside stall food. Worth it to buy. Theres only one minus, because the stall is on the side of the road. And coincidentally, the road is one of the main roads frequently passed by tourists and local residents. So its noisy, sorry. Hey.. Heyy one more thing. IF YOU COME HERE, JUST COME IN THE AFTERNOON. IF ITS AFTER MAGHRIB, WOW, BE READY TO BE PATIENT, THE WAIT IS LONG. QUEUE THE PROBLEM HEHEHEHEHE.

review_translated_text: Convenient location to get away from routine routine. the location is easy to reach with good road access. the service is friendly. the menu is varied and the taste is delicious. Access to vehicle parking is easy and simple with a fairly large parking area

review_text: Sudah lama ngga ke sini semenjak era covid. Ternyata masih bagus juga tempat ini. Jalanan masih sempit, tapi cukup enak, terawat. Asal kendaraan sehat, skill bukan pemula ya gampang aja mau pakai fwd cc kecil pun. Tiket masuk area Umbul Sidomukti per orang 5rb, parkir juga 5rb. Masih sangat terjangkau. Di sini menu cukup lengkap, harga agak pricey, tapi ya cukup worth it lah untuk wisata sesekali. Pelayanan ramah, cekatan juga, waktu tunggu dari pesan sampai siap saji ngga sampai setengah jam. Toilet bersih terawat, poin plus banget. Cocok banget untuk yg mau refreshing, pagi siang sore view nya bagus kalau pas ngga ada kabut.
review_translated_text: Havent been here for a long time since the Covid era. It turns out this place is still good. The roads are still narrow, but quite nice, well maintained. As long as the vehicle is healthy, the skills are not beginners, its easy to use even a small FWD CC. Entrance ticket to the Umbul Sidomukti area per person is 5 thousand, parking is also 5 thousand. Still very affordable. The menu here is quite complete, the prices are a bit pricey, but its quite worth it for an occasional trip. Friendly service, agile too, the waiting time from ordering to serving is less than half an hour. Clean, well-maintained toilets, a real plus point. Very suitable for those who want to refresh, morning, afternoon and evening the view is good if there is no fog.

Pelayanan ramah , tempat luas , bersih , parkir luas , kamar mandi bersih , ada musholla nya kecil bersih juga .. makanan enak semua , jujur kwetiaw nya enakk pake banget , gethuk bakar nya jg enak , minumannya seger n enak juga . Harga masih ramah . Kesini paling enak sama pasangan , keluarga or teman2 sekedar nongki n ngopi asyik . Semakin sore n jelang maghrib udara nya bikin melo pokoknya .
review_translated_text: Restaurant with panoramic views of the city of Ungaran, Bandungan and Mount Ungaran. Its really beautiful, especially coming here in the late afternoon... the air is cold, the atmosphere makes me tired. Friendly service, spacious place, clean, spacious parking, clean bathroom, there is a small clean prayer room too... all the food is delicious, honestly the kwetiaw is really delicious, the grilled gethuk is also delicious, the drinks are fresh and delicious too. Prices are still friendly. Its best to come here with your partner, family or friends just to hang out and drink coffee. As the afternoon gets closer to sunset, the air becomes mello.

Makanan : Untuk rasa makanan agak over dibagian saus  cabe & mayonais sehingga mengalahkan rasa yg lain, tapi ini kembali lagi ke selera, saya pribadi cenderung lebih suka rolls yang mungkin mirip-mirip kimbab asli dengan rasa yang simple dan tidak terlalu kompleks. Saya akan kembali lagi ke resto ini untuk mencoba menu lain yg sangat variatif dan inovatif. Layanan : Pelayanan sangat ramah dan sangat membantu termasuk merekomendasikan menu-menu yang jadi unggulan. Suasana : Tempat nyaman tapi sulit dijangkau kendaraan roda 4 dikarenakan tidak tersedianya area parkir yang memadai. Saran : sudah beberapa kali mencoba berkunjung tapi seringkali resto tutup, mungkin dapat lebih konsisten lagi terkait dengan jam atau hari buka. Menu-menu sangat inovatif, dengan promosi yang lebih masif sangat mungkin click rolls lebih berkembang lagi.
review_translated_text: Food: The taste of the food is a bit overdone in the chili sauce & mayonnaise section so that it overpowers the other flavors, but this comes back to taste, I personally tend to prefer rolls which are probably similar to real kimbab with a simple taste and not too complex . I will return to this restaurant again to try other menus which are very varied and innovative. Service: Service is very friendly and very helpful, including recommending superior menus. Atmosphere: Comfortable place but difficult to reach by 4-wheeled vehicles due to lack of adequate parking area. Suggestion: Ive tried visiting several times but the restaurant is often closed, maybe you could be more consistent regarding opening hours or days. The menus are very innovative, with more massive promotions it is possible for click rolls to develop even more.

The snacks are delicious, but for drinking, I think its standard, and unfortunately its not environmentally friendly because the drinks are served in plastic cups. Apart from that, there are several dirty spots, perhaps because some of the buildings are still under renovation. But overall, this place is quite comfortable and highly recommended.

review_text: Favorit disini cemilannya sih, terutama mix platter. Belum nemuu yang isinya se-worthed disini. Yang udah aku coba: 1. Mix platter: potato wedges, pangsit ayam, mozarella goreng, sosis. enak smuaa 2. onion ring . enak, crispy 3. Es cappucino. enak. Dominan kopi drpd susu 4. Es susu stoberi. Susu + potongan buah stoberi yg dibuat kayak selai? entah.. tp enak sih. ada kecut2 segernya. katanya itu signature nya sini 5. Mint lemonade : kayak virgin mojito tapi ga pake soda. enak jugaa 6. Salted caramel machiato; best coffee (menurut seleraku) 7. Mie: udah enak bumbunya cm sayang, pake (entah oregano / basil) jd rasanya nabrak antara jawa sm western 8. Nasgor kari: lumayan. Bumbu ky nasi kebuli / nasi biryani india 9. Cheese burger: enak, roti & patty empuk, bumbu pas. 10. Mojito; smua varian enak & seger 11. Fried dimsum ; enaaaak. Crispy. Pangsit isi ayam (di mix platter juga ada) Overall enak smua, tapi dari segi tempat mungkin ga terlalu luas ya. Tapi lumayan lah. Cuma utk waktu penyajian makanan agak lama. Mungkin bisa ditingkatkan
review_translated_text: My favorite snacks here are, especially the mix platter. Havent found anything as worthy as the content here. What Ive tried: 1. Mix platter: potato wedges, chicken dumplings, fried mozzarella, sausage. its all delicious 2. onion rings . delicious, crispy 3. Iced cappuccino. nice. Coffee dominates over milk 4. Strawberry milk ice. Milk + sliced strawberries made like jam? I dont know... but its delicious. theres a fresh sourness. he said thats his signature here 5. Mint lemonade: like a virgin mojito but without soda. delicious too 6. Salted caramel machiato; best coffee (according to my taste) 7. Noodles: the seasoning is delicious, unfortunately, I use (either oregano/basil) so the taste is somewhere between Javanese and Western 8. Nasgor curry: not bad. Seasoning like kebuli rice / Indian biryani rice 9. Cheese burger: delicious, soft bread & patty, perfect seasoning. 10. Mojitos; all variants are delicious & fresh 11. Fried dimsum; great. Crispy. Dumplings filled with chicken (mix platter also available) Overall its all delicious, but in terms of space it might not be too big. But its not bad. Only the food serving time is a bit long. Maybe it could be improved

review_text: Pertama kali kesini. Tempatnya di lantai 2, cukup nyaman, tapi sayang bagian indoornya kecil. Wajar karna cafe baru mungkin jd perlu waktu untuk memperluas tempatnya, semoga kedepannya diperluas dan lebih nyaman.Soal review akan ada welcome drink, mmm...idk, tp sejauh yg diliat ngga ada sih  . Untuk menu, sayang ya menu makanannya kurang bervariasi, lebih banyak minuman, mungkin karna peruntukannya buat nongkrong aja. Tapi dg menu yg sedikitpun pelayanannya cukup lama. Setengah jam lebih nunggu minuman keluar, dan masih harus nunggu setengah jam lagi nunggu makanan keluar sedangkan pengunjungnya ngga ramai.Total nunggu kurleb 1jam an . Kecewanya lagi, udah setengah jam nunggu makanan keluar, ada menu yg ternyata kosong dan ngga diinfoin ke customer (pas pesen ngga ada info kosong utk salah satu menu makanan itu) dan baru diinfoin ketika customer ambil makanannya di pelayanan dekat kasir. Alhasil harus nunggu lagi bbrp menit makanan dibuat dan dijanjin nanti dianterin ke meja, ternyata masih harus ambil sendiri lagi . Ekspektasi makanan keluar lama banget itu berharapnya anget karna baru diolah, ternyata dingin  . Soal minuman juga cukup bertanya2, apakah memang konsep minumannya less sugar? Karna yg diterima bener2 less less sugar /tawar  (mencoba positive thinking). Es teh ga ada manisnya, Coffe base (capucino & caffe late) yg diterima juga ga ada manisnya karna pahit kopi banget (saya memang bukan pecinta kopi, dan gapaham soal cita rasa kopi, tp menu yg sama ditempat lain lebih masuk dilidah). Semoga kedepannya lebih baik lagi ekuivalen coffe. Sarannya tingkatkan pelayanannya dan manajemen dapurnya karna untuk waktu tunggu 1jam itu lama dan akan buat pengunjung kecewa , tambah menu makanan lagi agar lebih bervariasi, untk minumannya sy ngga tau nih apakah karna ada kesalahan atau memang less sugar. Mungkin bisa diperbaiki lg ya. Saran lainnya kalau emang ada menu yg ternyata baru habis, bisa lah datengin customer dan tanyain mau diganti apa, soalnya kan udah bayar diawal yg harusnya menunya udah dipastin tersedia. Jangan baru pas cust ambil baru dikasih tau. Lama lagi lah kami nunggunya. Untuk saat ini prefer ke tempat sebelah dulu yg udah pasti pasti aja. Pengalaman pertama yg cukup mengecewakan sih. Semoga  bisa dijadikan masukan pihak owner dan management agar lebih baik lagi dalam memberikan pengalaman yg menyenangkan untuk customer.
review_translated_text: First time here. The place is on the 2nd floor, quite comfortable, but unfortunately the indoor part is small. Its normal because a new cafe might need time to expand the space, hopefully in the future it will be expanded and more comfortable. As for the review, there will be a welcome drink, mmm...idk, but as far as I can see there isnt any  . As for the menu, its a shame that the food menu is less varied, there are more drinks, maybe because its intended just for hanging out. But even with a small menu, the service takes quite a long time. Waited more than half an hour for the drinks to come out, and still had to wait another half hour for the food to come out even though there werent many people. The total wait was around 1 hour. What was even more disappointing was that I had been waiting for half an hour for the food to come out, there was a menu which turned out to be empty and the customer had not been informed (when ordering there was no empty information for one of the food menus) and this was only informed when the customer took his food at the service near the cashier. As a result, I had to wait a few more minutes for the food to be made and promised to be delivered to the table, but it turned out I still had to pick it up myself . The expectation was that the food would take a long time to come out, hoping it would be warm because it had just been prepared, but it turned out to be cold  . Regarding drinks, I also have to ask, is the concept of the drink really less sugar? Because what is received is really less sugar / tasteless (trying positive thinking). The iced tea didnt have any sweetness, the coffee base (cappuccino & coffee late) that was received also didnt have any sweetness because the coffee was very bitter (Im not a coffee lover, and dont understand the taste of coffee, but the same menu at other places is more palatable). Hopefully in the future the coffee will be even better. The suggestion is to improve the service and kitchen management because a 1 hour waiting time is long and will make visitors disappointed, add more food menus to make it more varied, as for the drinks, I dont know whether its because of an error or if theres just a lack of sugar. Maybe it can be repaired again. Another suggestion is that if there is a menu that has just run out, you can go to the customer and ask what they want to replace, because if you have paid in advance the menu should already be available. Dont just let the customer know when you pick it up. Weve been waiting a long time. For now, prefer to go to the place next door, which is certain. The first experience was quite disappointing. Hopefully this can be used as input for the owner and management to be even better at providing a pleasant experience for customers.

review_text: Tempat cukup nyaman, strategis, bersih tak terlalu jauh dengan monumen Susu Tumpah Boyolali, sekitar 250 meter ke arah barat di Jalan Teratai. Ada tempat cuci tangan di luar, ada wastafel di area pojokan kanan saat masuk ke area dalam, tersedia toilet juga. Menu masakan jawa seperti gudeg, sambal goreng, aneka lauk tahu, tempe, ikan, ayam, sop galantin, sop matahari, rice bowl, capcay, kwetiau, ada juga camilan berupa mendoan, pisang goreng, singkong goreng, dll. Minuman ada teh, jeruk, kopi, kopi susu, non kopi, moktail. Pelayanan ramah, sopan juga tanggap. Ada tanaman mostera yang cukup besar di pojokan dekat pintu masuk sebagai aksen pemanis ruangan. Saat siang melanda ruangan terasa panas karna beratap galvalum meski dilapisi paranet. Selamat mencoba bersantap bersama kawan, keluarga atau sahabat mu di sini...
review_translated_text: The place is quite comfortable, strategic, clean, not too far from the Boyolali Spilled Milk monument, about 250 meters to the west on Jalan Teratai. There is a hand washing place outside, there is a sink in the right corner area when you enter the inside area, there are toilets too. Javanese dishes such as gudeg, fried chili sauce, various side dishes of tofu, tempeh, fish, chicken, galantin soup, sun soup, rice bowl, capcay, kwetiau, there are also snacks in the form of mendoan, fried banana, fried cassava, etc. Drinks include tea, orange juice, coffee, milk coffee, non-coffee, mocktails. Friendly, polite and responsive service. There is a fairly large mustard plant in the corner near the entrance as a sweetening accent for the room. When midday hit, the room felt hot because it had a galvalum roof even though it was covered in paranet. Enjoy dining with your friends, family or friends here...

But yesterday there wasnt a trash can for throwing away drink wrappers in the room, maybe tomorrow it will be fixed. In terms of taste, its delicious and fresh. Yesterday I bought the August 17 promo. When I tried it there was a slight bitter taste in the berry taste. I dont know where it comes from and it makes my tongue ache like that. Maybe tomorrow we can fix the bitter taste. If the mango taste is enough, there is no strange taste according to the taste of mango. Recommended for those of you who are looking for something fresh and at a price that suits your pocket... come here and try it with your friends

review_text: When I first opened, I thought the service would be fast, but it turned out to be the same When breaking the fast yesterday the cooking taste was the same and many people didnt have ice cream and it was rarely ready
Good place and best service

Menu : - Fish and Chips nya bikin kaget, lebih cocok disebut mendoan ikan - Menu yg lain belum coba, Americano so so lah karena harga nya juga affordable Service : - Saat pesan menu sih sudah lumayan, staff nya informatif, proactive juga utk mempersilahkan cari tempat duduk dan ditungguin saat pesan menu - Staff di kasir yg perlu banyak improvement, khususnya ekspresi wajah, pilihan kata, dan intonasi bicara. Ohya dikasir juga tidak available QRIS, cashless hanya transfer via Bank. Ada tempelan logo shopee pay namun entah kenapa staf di kasir tidak mengenalkannya (kurang informatif) Atmoshpere : 1. Suasana joglo enak dengan furniture classic, dan tempat yg cukup teduh 2. Fasilitas mulai dari parkir, mushola, toilet, variasi tempat duduk semuanya bagus. Minus minim colokan, untung staff inisiatif untuk menyiapkan roll kabel Kesimpulan : Cocok buat nongkrong sama teman Buat kerja (WFC) kurang, minim colokan, wifi lemot, dan design meja kursi kurang sesuai utk dipakai nulis/buka laptop. Score : 3,67/5
review_translated_text: Menus: - The fish and chips are surprising, its more suitable to be called mendoan ikan - Havent tried the other menu, Americano is so so because the price is also affordable Services: - When ordering the menu its not bad, the staff is informative, proactive and also asks you to find a seat and wait for you to order the menu - Staff at the cashier need a lot of improvement, especially facial expressions, word choice and speaking intonation. Oh yes, the cashier also doesnt have QRIS available, cashless only transfers via bank. There is a Shopee Pay logo attached but for some reason the staff at the cashier doesnt introduce it (not very informative) Atmosphere: 1. The joglo atmosphere is nice with classic furniture and a fairly shady place 2. Facilities ranging from parking, prayer room, toilets, seating variations are all good. Minus the lack of plugs, fortunately the staff took the initiative to prepare a cable roll Conclusion : Suitable for hanging out with friends Not enough for work (WFC), minimal plugs, slow WiFi, and the desk and chair design is not suitable for writing/opening a laptop. Score: 3.67/5

review_text: Sebelumnya maav dan semoga kritikan dan saran saya membangun ada beberapa point penting untuk penjual terhadap makanan nya. Nilai + 1. Makanan & minuman harga murah 2. Banyak paket promo yg di aplikasi 3. Porsinya juga banyak tidak pelit 4. Rasa bisa di sesuaikann 5. Kalo kasih topping jg banyak 6. Lebih sering pake aplikasi dripda datang langsung karna banyak promo Nilai - 1. Kulit wortel kadang ditemukan tidak dikupas dan ujung bagian wortel yg ada daun nya juga ikut, potongan nya kurang rapi 2. Rasa nasgor ada yg terlalu asin 3. Kadang ditemukan jg ayam nya kurang matang atau kurang berasa 4. Kadang juga rasa ayam nya terlalu asin 5. Tempatnya jg terlalu kecil (karna konsep warkop) semoga ke dpn nya penjual nya bisa cari tempat yg lebih besar dan parkir yg memadai
response_from_owner_text: Terimakasih atas kritik dan sarannya semoga kami bisa selalu meningkatkan kwalitas dan layanan kami... Tapi maaf banget bahwa semua menu kami tidak ada satu pun yg menggunakan wortel. Dan belum pernah kami memasak menu di resto kami yg menggunakan wortel kak...di menu kami sayur hanya ada kol,sawi,dan tomat...mohon maaf apa bener sudah betul pesanan yg anda kritik tsb bener- bener menu dari resto kami?
review_translated_text: First of all, sorry and I hope my criticism and suggestions are constructive, there are several important points for sellers regarding their food. Value + 1. Cheap food & drinks 2. There are many promo packages in the application 3. The portions are also large and not stingy 4. The taste can be adjusted 5. If you add lots of toppings 6. Use the Dripda application more often, come directly because there are lots of promos Mark - 1. Carrot skin is sometimes found not peeled and the end of the part of the carrot with the leaves is also included, the cut is not neat 2. The taste of nasgor is too salty 3. Sometimes it is also found that the chicken is undercooked or lacks taste 4. Sometimes the chicken tastes too salty 5. The place is also too small (because of the warkop concept) hopefully in the future the seller can find a bigger place and adequate parking
response_from_owner_translated_text: Thank you for your criticism and suggestions. Hopefully we can always improve our quality and service... But Im really sorry that none of our menus use carrots. And weve never cooked a menu in our restaurant that uses carrots, bro... on our vegetable menu we only have cabbage, mustard greens and tomatoes... Im sorry, is it true that the order you are criticizing is really a menu from our restaurant?

I ordered grilled chicken but when it was ready it turned out to be grilled fried chicken. And the chili sauce is geprek chili sauce. For taste, 3 stars. response_from_owner_translated_text: Yes, sis... If there are a lot of queues or groups ordering different menus, you have to be a bit patient... But if you dont have to queue, thats fine... Hehehe... & for space & parking, dont compare it to a 5 star restaurant because Our stall, Warkop, is usually a 3 star, which is fine compared to a 5 star restaurant....hahaha... & for the grilled chicken, try it, if you really feel it, its really delicious, bro... Bens Cafe & Resto. Tempat nyaman, bersih dengan penataan ruangan yang bagus. Pelayanan ramah. Menyediakan berbagai menu makanan dan minuman. Tersedia juga tempat duduk luar ruangan. Memiliki tempat parkir yang luas. Dengan harga makanan dan minuman yang lumayan terjangkau. Cocok untuk tempat ngobrol santai bersama teman dan pasangan. Memiliki akses jalan yang bagus karena berada di tengah-tengah kota Bandungan. Bersebelahan dengan deretan cafe, warung dan toko perlengkapan rumah tangga dan kebutuhan sehari-hari. .......................................................... .......................................................... .......................................................... .......................................................... -    .
review_translated_text: Bens Cafe & Resto. Comfortable, clean place with good room layout. Friendly service. Provides various food and drink menus. Outdoor seating is also available. Has a large parking area. With fairly affordable food and drink prices. Suitable for a relaxed chat with friends and partners. It has good road access because it is in the middle of Bandungan city. Next to a row of cafes, stalls and shops for household goods and daily necessities. ................................................................ ........ ................................................................ ........ ................................................................ ........ ................................................................ ........ -    .

review_text: Tempat mudah dijangkau, nyaman dan bersih walaupun sedikit bising. Di menu Bens cappucino yang saya pesan, jauh dari ekspektasi awal dimana si barista bilang rasa kopinya lebih strong daripada yang original, tapi nyatanya rasanya cenderung ke susu hangat yang kemanisan (gula tidak dicampur sendiri oleh tamu) tidak ada rasa pahit kopinya. Spaghetti bolognese pun juga porsi terbilang sedikit dan terlalu matang, saus bolognese pun seperti saus bolognese instan yg dijual di pasaran.
review_translated_text: The place is easy to reach, comfortable and clean although a little noisy. On the Bens cappuccino menu that I ordered, it was far from initial expectations where the barista said the coffee taste was stronger than the original, but in fact the taste tended to be sweetened warm milk (sugar was not mixed by the guest himself) there was no bitter coffee taste. The spaghetti bolognese was also a bit small in portion and overcooked, the bolognese sauce was like the instant bolognese sauce sold on the market.

review_text: 1) Untuk tempat oke. Luas dan vibes nya asik banget apalagi kalau ada live music malam Minggu. Cocok buat nongkrong anak muda. 2)Tapi sorry not sorry, untuk harga makanan dan minuman termasuk over price, karena dari segi rasa, penampilan, dan quantity yang tersaji; -Fish & chip (24K), ikannya hanya dipotong2 kecil (4-5potong) dan rasa juga asin, porsi kentangnya sedikit. -Toast nya juga manggangnya kurang lama jadi gak begitu kerasa. Isiannya juga berantakan. -Matcha latte  (19K)kurang berasa green tea nya, terlalu milky. -Java Tea (16K), kurang enak untuk ukuran teh, hanya manis saja. Semoga ada perbaikan dari segi menu dan harga ya. Sayang sekali, padahal jatuh hati sama suasana halaman belakangnya . Sukses terus untuk DRutanz!
review_translated_text: 1) For the place okay. Its spacious and has a really cool vibe, especially when theres live music on Saturday nights. Suitable for hanging out with young people. 2) But sorry, not sorry, the prices of food and drinks are overpriced, because in terms of taste, appearance and quantity served; -Fish & chips (24K), the fish is only cut into small pieces (4-5 pieces) and the taste is also salty, the portion of potatoes is small. -The toast wasnt baked for long enough so it wasnt really tasty. The filling is also messy. -Matcha latte (19K) doesnt taste like green tea, its too milky. -Java Tea (16K), not very tasty for tea, only sweet. Hopefully there will be improvements in terms of menu and prices. Its a shame, even though I fell in love with the atmosphere in the back yard . Continued success for DRutanz!

review_text: Beli Esteh Indonesia karna owner nya mba Gigi Istri Sultan Andaraaa. Top sihhh menurut saya dengan harga 19k cup size nya besar pwolll utk varian Chizu Red Velvet rekomend. Saran saya sih mungkin manis nya kurangin dikit deh terlalu manis banget soal nya. review_translated_text: Buy Esteh Indonesia because the owner is Ms. Gigi, wife of Sultan Andaraa. Willing to travel all the way from Kebumen to Purworejo to try Esteh Indonesia   Overall the taste is unique, sweet, savory, and if you drink just a little, the taste will leave an impression on your tongue and wont disappear. In my opinion, its top notch, with a price of 19k, the cup size is really big for the recommended Chizu Red Velvet variant. My suggestion is maybe reduce the sweetness a bit, its too sweet. The service is fast, but its a shame that drinking at the place isnt very comfortable because its very close to the main road. Suggestions, its better to take away, guys.

review_text: Harap sabar ya kalau makan disini wkwk Antrian sering panjang, biasanya yang warga lokal bandungan didahulukan, malah ada yg dibolehkan ngambil kuah dan lauk sendiri, pokoknya harap maklum saja bagi yang pertama kali kesini wkwk Masakan dan gorengan enak-enak semua. Buka mulai jam 11 malam atau sebisanya yang jual. Saran : kalau pesen pakai basa jawa krama pasti ga dikepruk harga. Wkwkwkw R&D Vegetarian options: Ada pecel juga. Dietary restrictions: Halal. review_translated_text: Please be patient when eating here hahaha The queues are often long, usually local Bandungan residents are given priority, some are even allowed to take their own soup and side dishes, just be advised for those who are here for the first time hahaha All the dishes and fried foods are delicious. There is no definite price per portion, the main thing is that eating in moderation is definitely not expensive. There is a slight difference in calculated prices for Javanese-speaking and Indonesian-speaking customers, so thats understandable and normal hahaha Oh yes, the correct location is near RM Indra Mulya. Open from 11pm or whatever sells. Advice: if you order using Javanese language, dont worry about the price. hahahaha R&D Vegetarian options: Theres pecel too. Parking: Parking near Bandungan square.

review_text: Villa berbentuk rumah karena yang bersangkutan menyewakan rumahnya untuk jadi villa, fasilitas sudah komplit termasuk air panas, dan dapat motor untuk berkeliling selama menginap. Hal yang sangat disayangkan dari menginap disana adalah terkait kompor gas yang sulit dinyalakan dan karena pemilik tidak tinggal di sekitar lokasi villa apabila kendala hanya bisa dihubungi via whatsapp. Pengalaman kami disana gasnya habis begitu juga gas cadangannya. Karena pemilik tidak tinggal disana gasnya tidak bisa diganti dan kami menggunakan gas dari heater sehingga kami mandi air dingin.
review_translated_text: The villa is in the form of a house because the person concerned rents out his house to become a villa, the facilities are complete including hot water, and you can get a motorbike to get around during your stay. The most unfortunate thing about staying there is that the gas stove is difficult to turn on and because the owner does not live near the villa location, if there are problems, he can only be contacted via WhatsApp. In our experience there, the gas ran out and so did the reserve gas. Because the owner didnt live there the gas couldnt be replaced and we used gas from the heater so we took cold showers.

One thing that is unfortunate is that there are only two tables, so if you dont get a table you have to sit down in the window of a nearby shop.

review_translated_text: Actually, I like the concept of the place... But when I got confused with the menu, it turned out there was only 1 menu choice, coffee and milk with palm sugar/hazelnut/caramel... When I came here in the afternoon I wanted to drink coffee but it wasnt open yet... It was a bit late in the day... even though the view in the afternoon is better here... There was an angkringan next night... Only we didnt enjoy the angkringan because we had already eaten... The coffee tastes great... the price is 13k, maybe Ill order 2 coffees for 26k...
response_from_owner_translated_text: Sorry sis.. we only have classic and manual brewing menus.. hehe, next time try our mocktail menu too sis.. thanks for reviewing..

review_text: Kedai kopi di kota Boyolali. 5 menit dari pusat kota. Meski di tengah pemukiman, mudah ditemukan dengan @google map. Tempat aesthetic . Nyaman, wols. Indoor & outdoor. Bersih rapi. Smoking area. Es kopi susu , manual brew (arabica & Robusta), non Coffee, dll . Snack . Makanan berat . Harga kategori murah . Low end . Disediakan 2 gitar dan kajon . Baik & ramah . Parkir mobil agak terbatas , sepeda motor masih bisa . #CobainSkuy !
review_translated_text: Coffee shop in Boyolali city. 5 minutes from city center. Even though it is in the middle of a residential area, it is easy to find with @google map. Aesthetic place. Comfortable, woolly. Indoor & outdoor. Neatly clean. Smoking area. Iced milk coffee, manual brew (arabica & Robusta), non coffee, etc. Snacks . Heavy food. Cheap category prices. Low end. 2 guitars and cajon provided. Kind & friendly. Car parking is a bit limited, motorbikes are still available. #TrySkuy!

Usually signature coffee doesnt suit our palate just for fun and this is a recommendation... Unfortunately, the place inside is still mixed with a smoking area... So when you enter it smells like cigarette smoke... Yes, its true that there are some people who are not sensitive to cigarette smoke in the room... Payment can use QRiS.. Parking is a bit difficult, especially for cars on the side of the road... Hopefully it will always be busy... Yes... its a shame the coffee is often closed... Ive been here a few times and its always closed... I checked the Go Food was open which means the cafe is open...

Salah satu cafe kekinian di Purworejo. Tempatnya asyikk, ada live music juga, tapi sayang ketika saya selesai dinner jam 8 malam, baru mulai siap2 untuk live musicnya. Untuk makanan sebenernya gk ada yg spesial, sy pesan nasi ayam goreng + lalapan ternyata yg datang paha atas berukuran kecil, bahkan anak sy yg berumur 9 th pun gak kenyang sama sekali Nah yg sy acungin jempol itu rice bowl ayam sambal matahnya, pedesnyaaa.. bener bener juaraaa OK, i think this is the best dish in here, thumbs up Btw ada saran nih buat mba2 bag.dapur, next klo ada orderan wedang sereh & minta gula arennya dipisah, disajikan ke tamunya jangan gula aren yg segede gaban ya. Saya request ke salah seorang waitressnya biar dipotong kecil2, but mbanya malah ngejawab ya biasanya klo disini kami servenya memang bongkahan besar seperti itu pak. Sungguh ajib jawabannya FOOD: 7.5 DRINK: 7.0 SERVICE: 6.5 PLACE: 8.5 PRICE: 7.5 AVERAGE: 7.4 GOOD Parking: Parkirannya luasss, muat banyak mobil.. Mungkin ini salah satu tempat makan di PWR yg parkiran mobilnya nyaman   Lebih nyaman lagi jika di bagian atasnya ada ditutup galvalum sehingga mobil dan motor tidak kehujanan, bakal menambah nilai plus dari sebelumnya.
review_translated_text: One of the contemporary cafes in Purworejo. The place is fun, there is live music too, but unfortunately when I finished dinner at 8 pm, I was just starting to get ready for the live music. As for the food, there really isnt anything special, I ordered fried chicken rice + fresh vegetables but the thighs that came were small, even my 9 year old child wasnt full at all Well, the one I give the thumbs up to is the chicken rice bowl with sambal matah, its really spicy... its really a winner OK, I think this is the best dish in here, thumbs up BTW, I have a suggestion for ladies and gentlemen, next time you order wedang lemongrass & ask for the palm sugar to be separated, dont serve the palm sugar as big as the gaban. I asked one of the waitresses to cut it into small pieces, but the lady answered, yes, usually when we serve it here its big chunks like that, sir. Its really a great answer FOOD: 7.5 DRINK: 7.0 SERVICE: 6.5 PLACE: 8.5 PRICE: 7.5 AVERAGE: 7.4 GOOD Parking: The parking lot is spacious, fits lots of cars.. Maybe this is one of the places to eat at PWR where the car parking is comfortable   It would be even more comfortable if the top was covered with galvalum so that cars and motorbikes dont get caught in the rain, it would add a plus point than before.

review_text: The atmosphere is cozy for a party, the live music is really good, I like the sound too. Its a shame because the meaning is not very complete and there are no other types of coffee. The rice bowl is delicious. Suggestion: expand the menu and if possible, have a batista specifically for GT coffee, for those who like coffee, this is not recommended. Payment is still only in cash, no cash yet

review_text: Kalau ke Purworejo maka seolah kewajiban kami mesti mampir ke tempat ini. Hal ini sudah kami lakukan selama belasan tahun. Geblek gorengnya gurih, kalau dimakan selagi hangat sambil dicocolkan ke sambel kacang atau saos dicampur sedikit kecap, ehm enak benar. Gorengan lain juga gurih, krispi,  pas benar yang memberi bumbu. Ukurannya juga besar. Dimakan begitu saja atau dijadikan lauk makan, rasanya tetap maknyus. Seingatku yang jual sudah berganti orang, mungkin dulu orang tua dan sekarang anaknya, tapi rasa gorengnya tetap. Silakan mampir
review_translated_text: If we go to Purworejo then it seems like our obligation to stop by this place. We have been doing this for dozens of years. The fried geblek is delicious, if you eat it while its warm while dipping it in peanut sauce or sauce mixed with a little soy sauce, its really delicious. Other fritters are also tasty, crispy, just the right amount of spice. The size is also big. Eat it just like that or use it as a side dish, it still tastes delicious. As far as I remember, the people selling it have changed, maybe first the parents and now the children, but the fried taste remains. Please stop by

review_text: Gorengan legendaris ini awalnya berjualan di pinggir jalan, kemudian pindah ke gang sebelah SD Maria, dan sekarang di halaman rumah dinas Pos Indonesia. Gorengan yg tersedia mulai dari tempe, tahu isi, pisang, dan geblek. Rasanya masih konsisten sampai sekarang, meskipun sudah turun ke generasi kedua. Harga sangat terjangkau dengan porsi gorengan yg cukup besar. Buka mulai jam 4 sore.
review_translated_text: This legendary fried food was initially sold on the side of the road, then moved to the alley next to Maria Elementary School, and now in the yard of the Pos Indonesia official residence. The available fried foods range from tempeh, stuffed tofu, banana and geblek. The taste is still consistent today, even though it has gone down to the second generation. Prices are very affordable with quite large portions of fried food. Open from 4pm.

review_text: Jaman sejak 80an, Udah ada nih. Geblek Kantor Pos. LEGENDA!

review_text: Geblek legendaris yang ada di Purworejo. Jika Anda berburu makanan khas Purworejo, seperti gorengan geblek, saya sarankan Anda harus berkunjung ke tempat ini. Sudah ada sejak tahun 90 an hingga sekarang berganti generasi ke generasi. Suara gas yang menderu-deru membuat nuansa khas aroma gorengan geblek.
review_translated_text: The legendary geblek in Purworejo. If you are looking for typical Purworejo food, such as fried geblek, I suggest you visit this place. It has been around since the 90s until now, changing from generation to generation. The sound of roaring gas creates the distinctive aroma of fried geblek.

review_translated_text: Bandungan market is new, looks wider and nicer...there is culinary delights here at night, unfortunately it was quiet when I got there...maybe because it was raining... there are those selling snacks, and heavy food, and wedang too, but as far as I can see, no one is selling rabbit satay, or chicken... the prices are still reasonable, even though there is no price list, they dont give arbitrary prices (meatballs 18 thousand, wedang ronde 10 thousand, tea 2 thousand) the maintenance of the place needs to be improved, for example the toilet, it smells a bit... the parking is quite spacious... and the air is really cold at night....its also fun, if you feel hot in Semarang, you can stop by here....

review_text: Ordered through food delivery apps. Dimsums are actually taste great, but kinda disappointed because they came out different like how they pictured them on the app. I was expecting kinds of dim sum, but what I got was all the same (same color, same shape, same taste). Also they don t give you sambal sauce which is a big miss on.  I wish they could improve on that, because the dim sum tastes quite great.
response_from_owner_text: Terima kasih atas masukannya, Mbak. Untuk yang varian seperti isi telur puyuh ( kulit warba hijau) dan isi udang ( kulit warna kuning ) memang belum memproduski banyak. Dan pas tadi mbak pesan lewat grab food pas 2 varian itu habis. Untuk saos sambal, akan kami sediakan setelah ini. Sekali lagi kami minta maaf atas kekecewaan yang Mbak Tiara alami. Dan terima kasih banyak atas saran dan kritiknya. Mungkin kalau ada waktu, Mbak Tiara bisa mampir ke outlet kami ( jl urip sumoharjo depan murah cell  selatan sentral parabola ) supaya kami nanti bisa sedikit mengobati rasa kekecewaan Mbak Tiara
response_from_owner_translated_text: Thank you for your input, Sis. Variants such as quail egg filling (green shell) and shrimp filling (yellow shell) dont produce many. And just now, Sis ordered via Grab Food when the 2 variants were out of stock. For chili sauce, we will provide it after this. Once again we apologize for the disappointment that Mbak Tiara experienced. And thank you very much for the suggestions and criticism. Maybe if you have time, Mbak Tiara can stop by our outlet (Jl Urip Sumoharjo Front Cheap Cell South Central Parabola) so that we can relieve a little of Mbak Tiaras disappointment

review_text: Salah satu alternatif tempat sarapan di Bandungan. Lokasinya berada di sekitar alun-alun Bandungan, lebih tepatnya di emperan alfamart juga sebelah pos polisi terpadu Bandungan. Selain bubur juga ada pilihan nasi pecel atau nasi rames. Tentu saja yang paling khas disini adalah bubur opaknya. Bubur dituangkan di atas opak kemudian diberi toping sesuai pilihan kita. Toping default dari penjualnya biasanya sayuran, oseng tempe, kekian, bakmi, ditambah bumbu kacang. Kita juga bisa menambahkan tahu terik, telur ceplok, maupun gorengan. Bubur ini cukup mengenyangkan dan rasanya enak. Untuk harganya sendiri terbilang murah dan tergantung dari toping yang dipilih.
review_translated_text: One of the alternative breakfast places in Bandungan. The location is around the Bandungan square, more precisely in the Alfamart window and next to the Bandungan integrated police post. Apart from porridge, there is also a choice of pecel rice or rames rice. Of course, the most distinctive thing here is the opaque porridge. The porridge is poured over the opak and then given toppings of our choice. The sellers default toppings are usually vegetables, stir-fried tempeh, kekian, noodles, plus peanut sauce. We can also add hot tofu, fried eggs or fried foods. This porridge is quite filling and tastes delicious. The price itself is relatively cheap and depends on the toppings chosen.

review_translated_text: This is the first time Ive eaten here, using sticky rice. It turns out that in Boyolali the sticky rice is white sticky rice or not sticky rice tape. The dawet is white, because it doesnt use dye. There are 2 choices of sugar, use granulated sugar or Javanese sugar. Standard price, cheap. Maybe if you come here tomorrow, buy one that uses Javanese sugar. Quite full, because there is quite a lot of sticky rice

review_text: Dawet yang enak harga standar. Bagi yang kurang suka dawet dengan gula merah bisa coba di sini karena gulanya pakai gula pasir. Cendolnya berbahan pati onggok, atau tepung dari batang aren. Selain jualan dawet, di sini juga menjual soto tapi hanya pagi hari. Parking: Its quite difficult to park since its proximity in the sunggingan market and the road are too narrow.
review_translated_text: Delicious dawet at standard prices. For those who dont like dawet with brown sugar, you can try it here because the sugar is made from granulated sugar. The cendol is made from starch onggok, or flour from sugar palm stems. Apart from selling dawet, they also sell soto here but only in the morning. Parking: Its quite difficult to park since its proximity to the Sunggingan market and the road is too narrow.

One of the best HIK in Boyolali. It is also near of the city center. They sell some of the most soothing and refreshing beverages in Boyolali. Their Jahe is on point. It is perfectly balance between spiciness from the ginger, and sugary sweet. I always ordered their ginger tea. The combination of ginger and solos tea never gone wrong. Besides ginger, they also served various kinds of side dishes. Sate, packed rice, fritters, or anything you can think of angkringan.

The Ginger Milk is a winner, the ginger drink is unique, a must try. Standard angkringan food. This is a legendary angkringan in Boyolali, its been around for more than 30 years. Previously it was located opposite, now it has moved to the side so there is a place to eat (the building). In the past, the location was in front of the BPR and the meal was sitting on the floor with a tiker.
